WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:00.700
1.

00:00:14.980 --> 00:00:26.240
The Book of the Generation of Jesus Christ, the Son of David, the Son of Abraham.

00:00:26.240 --> 00:00:33.720
2. Abraham begat Isaac, and Isaac begat Jacob, and Jacob begat Judas and his brethren.

00:00:34.800 --> 00:00:43.700
3. And Judas begat Phares and Zerah of Tamar, and Phares begat Ezram, and Ezram begat Aram,

00:00:44.280 --> 00:00:52.360
and Aram begat Amenadab, and Amenadab begat Nason, and Nason begat Salmon, and Salmon

00:00:52.360 --> 00:01:00.660
begat Boaz of Rechab, and Boaz begat Obed of Ruth, and Obed begat Jesse.

00:01:01.940 --> 00:01:07.920
4. And Jesse begat David the king, and David the king begat Solomon of her that had been the wife

00:01:07.920 --> 00:01:18.460
of Uriah, and Solomon begat Roboam, and Roboam begat Abiah, and Abiah begat Asa, and Asa begat

00:01:19.100 --> 00:01:28.540
Josephat, and Josephat begat Joram, and Joram begat Ozias, and Ozias begat Joetham, and Joetham

00:01:28.540 --> 00:01:38.980
begat Achaz, and Achaz begat Ezekias, and Ezekias begat Manasseh, and Manasseh begat Amen, and Amen

00:01:38.980 --> 00:01:46.300
begat Josias, and Josias begat Jeconias and his brethren about the time they were carried away

00:01:46.300 --> 00:01:53.900
to Babylon, and after they were brought to Babylon, Jeconias begat Silatio, and Silatio

00:01:53.900 --> 00:02:04.280
begat Zerubbabel, and Zerubbabel begat Abiyud, and Abiyud begat Eliakim, and Eliakim begat Azor,

00:02:05.660 --> 00:02:15.440
and Azor begat Sadok, and Sadok begat Achim, and Achim begat Eliud, and Eliud begat Eliezer,

00:02:16.000 --> 00:02:24.760
and Eliezer begat Matan, and Matan begat Jacob, and Jacob begat Joseph, the husband of Mary,

00:02:25.060 --> 00:02:33.240
of whom was born Jesus, who was called Christ. So all the generations from Abraham to David

00:02:33.240 --> 00:02:40.640
are 14 generations, and from David until the carrying away into Babylon are 14 generations,

00:02:40.640 --> 00:02:49.400
and from the carrying away into Babylon unto Christ are 14 generations. Now the birth of Jesus

00:02:49.400 --> 00:02:57.020
Christ was on this wise. When as his mother Mary was espoused to Joseph, before they came together

00:02:57.020 --> 00:03:03.960
she was found with child of the Holy Ghost. Then Joseph, her husband, being a just man

00:03:03.960 --> 00:03:09.600
and not willing to make her a public example, was minded to put her away privily.

00:03:10.640 --> 00:03:16.100
But while he thought on these things, behold, the angel of the Lord appeared unto him in a dream,

00:03:16.260 --> 00:03:24.020
saying, Joseph, thou son of David, fear not to take unto thee Mary thy wife, for that which

00:03:24.020 --> 00:03:30.640
is conceived in her is of the Holy Ghost, and she shall bring forth the Son, and thou shalt call

00:03:30.640 --> 00:03:38.840
his name Jesus, for he shall save his people from their sins. Now all this was done that it might

00:03:38.840 --> 00:03:45.440
be fulfilled, which was spoken of the Lord by the prophet, saying, Behold, a virgin shall be with

00:03:45.440 --> 00:03:53.440
child, and shall bring forth a son, and they shall call his name Immanuel, which being interpreted

00:03:53.440 --> 00:04:00.940
is God with us. Then Joseph, being raised from sleep, did as the angel of the Lord had bidden him,

00:04:01.320 --> 00:04:08.240
and took unto him his wife, and knew her not, till she had brought forth her firstborn son,

00:04:08.240 --> 00:04:11.180
and he called his name Jesus.

00:04:31.670 --> 00:04:38.030
Now when Jesus was born in Bethlehem of Judea, in the days of Herod the king, behold, there

00:04:38.030 --> 00:04:44.970
came wise men from the east to Jerusalem, saying, Where is he that is born king of the

00:04:44.970 --> 00:04:50.210
have seen his star in the east, and are come to worship him?

00:04:50.450 --> 00:04:55.650
When Herod the king had heard these things, he was troubled, and all Jerusalem with him.

00:04:56.330 --> 00:05:01.770
And when he had gathered all the chief priests and scribes of the people together, he demanded

00:05:01.770 --> 00:05:03.710
of them where Christ should be born.

00:05:04.170 --> 00:05:10.390
And they said unto him, In Bethlehem of Judea, for thus it is written by the prophet, And

00:05:10.390 --> 00:05:16.470
thou, Bethlehem, in the land of Judea, art not the least among the princes of Judea,

00:05:16.490 --> 00:05:21.030
for out of thee shall come a governor that shall rule my people Israel.

00:05:21.630 --> 00:05:27.210
Then Herod, when he had privily called the wise men, inquired of them diligently at what

00:05:27.210 --> 00:05:28.490
time the star appeared.

00:05:29.290 --> 00:05:35.110
And he sent them to Bethlehem, and said, Go, and search diligently for the young child.

00:05:35.430 --> 00:05:42.290
And when ye have found him, bring me word again that I may come and worship him also.

00:05:42.870 --> 00:05:48.390
When they had heard the king, they departed, and lo, the star which they saw in the east

00:05:48.390 --> 00:05:52.990
went before them, till it came and stood over where the young child was.

00:05:53.650 --> 00:05:58.610
When they saw the star, they rejoiced with exceeding great joy.

00:05:59.350 --> 00:06:04.590
And when they were come into the house, they saw the young child with Mary his mother,

00:06:05.170 --> 00:06:07.850
and fell down, and worshipped him.

00:06:08.410 --> 00:06:13.550
And when they had opened their treasures, they presented unto him gifts, gold, frankincense,

00:06:13.670 --> 00:06:15.350
and myrrh.

00:06:15.450 --> 00:06:20.650
And being warned of God in a dream that they should not return to Herod, they departed

00:06:20.650 --> 00:06:22.790
into their own country another way.

00:06:23.210 --> 00:06:28.690
And when they were departed, behold, the angel of the Lord appeared to Joseph in a dream,

00:06:28.950 --> 00:06:34.810
saying, Arise, and take the young child and his mother, and flee into Egypt, and be thou

00:06:34.810 --> 00:06:36.450
there until I bring thee word.

00:06:36.910 --> 00:06:40.450
For Herod will seek the young child to destroy him.

00:06:40.850 --> 00:06:46.770
When he arose, he took the young child and his mother by night, and departed into Egypt.

00:06:47.550 --> 00:06:52.470
And was there until the death of Herod, that it might be fulfilled which was spoken of

00:06:52.470 --> 00:06:57.990
the Lord by the prophet, saying, Out of Egypt have I called my son.

00:06:58.910 --> 00:07:05.430
Then Herod, when he saw that he was mocked of the wise men, was exceeding wrath, and

00:07:05.430 --> 00:07:11.610
sent forth, and slew all the children that were in Bethlehem, and in all the coasts thereof,

00:07:11.890 --> 00:07:17.010
from two years old and under, according to the time which he had diligently inquired

00:07:17.010 --> 00:07:18.070
of the wise men.

00:07:18.590 --> 00:07:25.530
Then was fulfilled that which was spoken by Jeremy the prophet, saying, In Rama was there

00:07:25.530 --> 00:07:34.250
a voice heard, lamentation, and weeping, and great mourning, Rachel, weeping for her children,

00:07:34.730 --> 00:07:37.750
and would not be comforted, because they are not.

00:07:38.490 --> 00:07:43.830
But when Herod was dead, behold, an angel of the Lord appeared in a dream to Joseph

00:07:43.830 --> 00:07:50.130
in Egypt, saying, Arise, and take the young child and his mother, and go into the land

00:07:50.130 --> 00:07:55.050
of Israel, for they are dead which sought the young child's life.

00:07:55.990 --> 00:08:01.630
And he arose, and took the young child and his mother, and came into the land of Israel.

00:08:02.410 --> 00:08:07.990
But when he heard that Archelaus did reign in Judea in the room of his father Herod,

00:08:07.990 --> 00:08:13.090
he was afraid to go thither, notwithstanding being warned of God in a dream.

00:08:13.630 --> 00:08:19.790
He turned aside into the parts of Galilee, and he came and dwelt in a city called Nazareth,

00:08:20.310 --> 00:08:23.710
that it might be fulfilled which was spoken by the prophets.

00:08:24.390 --> 00:08:28.130
He shall be called a Nazarene.

00:08:49.815 --> 00:08:57.275
In those days came John the Baptist, preaching in the wilderness of Judea, and saying, Repent

00:08:57.275 --> 00:09:00.615
ye, for the kingdom of heaven is at hand.

00:09:01.535 --> 00:09:08.475
For this is he that was spoken of by the prophet Isaiah, saying, The voice of one crying in

00:09:08.475 --> 00:09:14.315
the wilderness, prepare ye the way of the Lord, make his path straight.

00:09:14.755 --> 00:09:20.335
And the same John had his raiment of camel's hair, and a leather girdle about his loins,

00:09:20.675 --> 00:09:23.835
and his meat was locusts and wild honey.

00:09:23.835 --> 00:09:30.995
Then went out to him Jerusalem and all Judea, and all the regions around about Jordan, and

00:09:30.995 --> 00:09:34.495
were baptized of him in Jordan confessing their sins.

00:09:35.235 --> 00:09:41.195
But when he saw many of the Pharisees and Sadducees come to his baptism, he said unto

00:09:41.195 --> 00:09:47.915
them, O generation of vipers, who hath warned you to flee from the wrath to come?

00:09:48.355 --> 00:09:55.335
Bring forth therefore fruits meet for repentance, and think not to say within yourselves, We

00:09:55.335 --> 00:09:57.235
have Abraham to our father.

00:09:57.915 --> 00:10:04.575
For I say unto you, that God is able of these stones to raise up children unto Abraham.

00:10:05.275 --> 00:10:09.775
And now also the axe is laid unto the root of the trees.

00:10:10.375 --> 00:10:16.635
Therefore every tree which bringeth not forth good fruit is hewn down and cast into the

00:10:16.635 --> 00:10:17.115
fire.

00:10:17.795 --> 00:10:21.895
I indeed baptize you with water unto repentance.

00:10:23.015 --> 00:10:29.235
But he that cometh after me is mightier than I, whose shoes I am not worthy to bear.

00:10:30.135 --> 00:10:37.715
He shall baptize you with the Holy Ghost, and with fire, whose fan is in his hand.

00:10:38.515 --> 00:10:44.275
And he will thoroughly purge his floor, and gather his wheat into the garner.

00:10:45.065 --> 00:10:49.675
But he will burn up the chaff with unquenchable fire.

00:10:50.455 --> 00:10:55.555
Then cometh Jesus from Galilee to Jordan unto John to be baptized of him.

00:10:56.115 --> 00:11:01.415
But John forbade him, saying, I have need to be baptized of thee.

00:11:02.395 --> 00:11:03.635
And comest thou to me?

00:11:04.375 --> 00:11:11.875
And Jesus answering said unto him, Suffer it to be so now, for thus it becometh us to

00:11:11.875 --> 00:11:13.375
fulfill all righteousness.

00:11:14.475 --> 00:11:15.935
Then he suffered him.

00:11:16.335 --> 00:11:21.095
And Jesus, when he was baptized, went up straight way out of the water.

00:11:21.715 --> 00:11:27.275
And lo, the heavens were opened unto him, and he saw the Spirit of God descending like

00:11:27.275 --> 00:11:30.055
a dove, and lighting upon him.

00:11:30.055 --> 00:11:38.475
And lo, a voice from heaven sang, This is my beloved Son, in whom I am well pleased.

00:11:58.029 --> 00:12:04.549
Then was Jesus led up of the Spirit into the wilderness to be tempted of the devil.

00:12:05.069 --> 00:12:10.549
And when he had fasted forty days and forty nights, he was afterward unhungered.

00:12:11.269 --> 00:12:17.229
And when the tempter came to him, he said, If thou be the Son of God, command that these

00:12:17.229 --> 00:12:19.169
stones be made bread.

00:12:20.129 --> 00:12:27.809
But he answered and said, It is written, Man shall not live by bread alone, but by every

00:12:27.809 --> 00:12:30.349
word that proceedeth out of the mouth of God.

00:12:31.389 --> 00:12:36.849
Then the devil taketh him up into the holy city, and setteth him on a pinnacle of the

00:12:36.849 --> 00:12:44.489
temple, and saith unto him, If thou be the Son of God, cast thyself down, for it is written,

00:12:45.189 --> 00:12:51.929
He shall give his angels charge concerning thee, and in their hands they shall bear thee

00:12:51.929 --> 00:12:56.069
up, lest at any time thou dash thy foot against a stone.

00:12:57.669 --> 00:13:04.389
Jesus said unto him, It is written again, Thou shalt not tempt the Lord thy God.

00:13:05.149 --> 00:13:11.689
Again the devil taketh him up into an exceeding high mountain, and showeth him all the kingdoms

00:13:11.689 --> 00:13:19.349
of the world, and the glory of them, and saith unto him, All these things I will give thee,

00:13:19.729 --> 00:13:23.609
if thou wilt fall down and worship me.

00:13:24.529 --> 00:13:31.169
Then saith Jesus unto him, Get thee hence, Satan, for it is written, Thou shalt worship

00:13:31.169 --> 00:13:35.289
the Lord thy God, and him only shalt thou serve.

00:13:36.189 --> 00:13:41.669
Then the devil leaveth him, and behold, angels came, and ministered unto him.

00:13:42.649 --> 00:13:48.029
Now when Jesus had heard that John was cast into prison, he departed into Galilee.

00:13:48.569 --> 00:13:53.489
And leaving Nazareth, he came and dwelt in Capernaum, which is upon the sea-coast, in

00:13:53.489 --> 00:13:59.349
the borders of Zebulun and Naphtalim, that it might be fulfilled which was spoken by

00:13:59.649 --> 00:14:06.649
the prophet, saying, The land of Zebulun and the land of Naphtalim, by the way of the sea,

00:14:06.969 --> 00:14:10.829
beyond Jordan, Galilee of the Gentiles.

00:14:11.829 --> 00:14:17.989
The people which sat in darkness saw a great light, and to them which sat in the region

00:14:17.989 --> 00:14:21.489
unshadowed of death, light has sprung up.

00:14:22.129 --> 00:14:29.269
From that time Jesus began to preach, and to say, Repent, for the kingdom of heaven

00:14:29.269 --> 00:14:30.309
is at hand.

00:14:31.369 --> 00:14:38.109
And Jesus walking by the sea of Galilee saw two brethren, Simon, called Peter, and Andrew,

00:14:38.129 --> 00:14:41.509
his brother, casting a net into the sea, for they were fishers.

00:14:41.909 --> 00:14:48.009
And he saith unto them, Follow me, and I will make you fishers of men.

00:14:48.849 --> 00:14:51.889
And they straightway left their nets and followed him.

00:14:52.829 --> 00:14:58.069
And going on from thence he saw two other brethren, James the son of Zebedee and John

00:14:58.069 --> 00:15:03.809
his brother, in a ship with Zebedee their father mending their nets, and he called them.

00:15:04.589 --> 00:15:09.529
And they immediately left the ship and their father, and followed him.

00:15:10.569 --> 00:15:16.409
And Jesus went about all Galilee, teaching in their synagogues, and preaching the gospel

00:15:16.409 --> 00:15:22.149
of the kingdom, and healing all manner of sickness, and all manner of disease among

00:15:22.149 --> 00:15:22.849
the people.

00:15:23.049 --> 00:15:29.089
And his fame went throughout all Syria, and they brought unto him all sick people that

00:15:29.089 --> 00:15:35.789
were taken with diverse diseases and torments, and those which were possessed with devils,

00:15:36.229 --> 00:15:42.909
and those which were lunatic, and those that had the palsy, and he healed them.

00:15:44.049 --> 00:15:49.569
And there followed him great multitudes of people, from Galilee, and from Decapolis,

00:15:49.589 --> 00:15:53.829
and from Jerusalem, and from Judea, and from beyond Jordan.

00:16:04.200 --> 00:16:23.300
V. And seeing the multitudes, he went up into a mountain, and when he was set, his disciples

00:16:23.300 --> 00:16:27.120
came unto him, and he opened his mouth and taught them, saying,

00:16:27.860 --> 00:16:35.640
Blessed are the poor in spirit, for theirs is the kingdom of heaven. Blessed are they that mourn,

00:16:37.060 --> 00:16:40.920
for they shall be comforted. Blessed are the meek,

00:16:42.560 --> 00:16:49.180
for they shall inherit the earth. Blessed are they which do hunger and thirst after righteousness,

00:16:50.040 --> 00:16:57.100
for they shall be filled. Blessed are the merciful, for they shall obtain mercy.

00:16:57.880 --> 00:17:05.280
Blessed are the pure in heart, for they shall see God. Blessed are the peacemakers,

00:17:05.360 --> 00:17:11.900
for they shall be called the children of God. Blessed are they which are persecuted for

00:17:11.900 --> 00:17:20.820
righteousness' sake, for theirs is the kingdom of heaven. Blessed are ye when men shall revile you

00:17:20.820 --> 00:17:26.580
and persecute you, and shall say all manner of evil against you falsely for my sake.

00:17:27.580 --> 00:17:35.120
Rejoice and be exceeding glad, for great is your reward in heaven, for so persecuted they the

00:17:35.120 --> 00:17:44.080
prophets which were before you. Ye are the salt of the earth, but if the salt have lost its savor,

00:17:44.700 --> 00:17:51.480
wherewith shall it be salted? It is thenceforth good for nothing, but to be cast out,

00:17:51.800 --> 00:17:59.880
and to be trodden under foot of men. Ye are the light of the world. A city that is set on a hill

00:17:59.880 --> 00:18:06.700
cannot be hid, neither do men light a candle and put it under a bushel, but on a candlestick,

00:18:06.900 --> 00:18:13.680
and it giveth light unto all that are in the house. Let your light so shine before men,

00:18:14.080 --> 00:18:21.020
that they may see your good works, and glorify your Father which is in heaven. Think not that

00:18:21.020 --> 00:18:29.700
I am come to destroy the law or the prophets, I am not come to destroy, but to fulfill. For verily

00:18:29.700 --> 00:18:37.960
I say unto you, till heaven and earth pass, one jot or one tittle shall in no wise pass from the

00:18:37.960 --> 00:18:45.940
law, till all be fulfilled. Whosoever therefore shall break one of these least commandments,

00:18:46.460 --> 00:18:53.380
and shall teach men so, he shall be called the least in the kingdom of heaven. But whosoever shall

00:18:53.380 --> 00:19:01.320
do and teach them, the same shall be called great in the kingdom of heaven. For I say unto you,

00:19:01.900 --> 00:19:07.720
that except your righteousness shall exceed the righteousness of the scribes and Pharisees, ye

00:19:07.720 --> 00:19:15.800
shall in no case enter into the kingdom of heaven. Ye have heard that it was said of them of old

00:19:15.800 --> 00:19:23.900
time, thou shalt not kill, and whoever shall kill shall be in danger of the judgment. But I say unto

00:19:23.900 --> 00:19:30.420
you, that whosoever is angry with his brother without a cause, shall be in danger of the

00:19:30.420 --> 00:19:38.480
judgment. And whosoever shall say to his brother, Rocka, shall be in danger of the council. But

00:19:38.480 --> 00:19:48.220
whosoever shall say, thou fool, shall be in danger of hell-fire. Therefore, if thou bring thy gift to

00:19:48.220 --> 00:19:54.420
the altar, and there rememberst that thy brother hath aught against thee, leave there thy gift

00:19:54.420 --> 00:20:01.320
before the altar, and go thy way, first be reconciled to thy brother, and then come and

00:20:01.320 --> 00:20:08.400
offer thy gift. Agree with thine adversary quickly, whilst thou art in the way with him,

00:20:08.820 --> 00:20:15.020
lest at any time the adversary deliver thee to the judge, and the judge deliver thee to the officer,

00:20:15.140 --> 00:20:22.300
and thou be cast into prison. Verily I say unto thee, thou shalt by no means come out thence,

00:20:22.300 --> 00:20:30.500
till thou hast paid the uttermost farthing. Ye have heard that it was said by them of old time,

00:20:30.800 --> 00:20:37.000
thou shalt not commit adultery. But I say unto you, that whosoever looketh on a woman to lust

00:20:37.000 --> 00:20:43.380
after her, hath committed adultery with her already in his heart. And if they write, I offend thee,

00:20:44.240 --> 00:20:49.920
pluck it out, and cast it from thee. For it is profitable for thee that one of thy members

00:20:49.920 --> 00:20:56.240
should perish, and not that thy whole body should be cast into hell. And if thy right hand offend

00:20:56.240 --> 00:21:03.000
thee, cut it off, and cast it from thee. For it is profitable for thee that one of thy members

00:21:03.000 --> 00:21:10.620
should perish, and not that thy whole body should be cast into hell. It hath been said, whosoever

00:21:10.620 --> 00:21:16.460
shall put away his wife, let him give her a writing of divorcement. But I say unto you,

00:21:16.460 --> 00:21:21.020
that whosoever shall put away his wife, saving for the cause of fornication,

00:21:22.020 --> 00:21:28.000
causeth her to commit adultery. And whosoever shall marry her, that is divorced, committeth

00:21:28.000 --> 00:21:35.220
adultery. Again ye have heard that it hath been said by them of old time, thou shalt not

00:21:35.220 --> 00:21:42.780
forswear thyself, but shalt perform unto the Lord thine oaths. But I say unto you, swear not at all,

00:21:42.780 --> 00:21:49.380
neither by heaven, for it is God's throne, nor by the earth, for it is his footstool,

00:21:49.600 --> 00:21:56.420
neither by Jerusalem, for it is the city of the great King. Neither shalt thou swear by thy head,

00:21:56.920 --> 00:22:04.260
because thou canst not make one hair white or black. But let your communication be yea, yea,

00:22:05.060 --> 00:22:09.820
nay, nay, for whatsoever is more than these cometh of evil.

00:22:11.140 --> 00:22:18.440
Ye have heard that it hath been said, an eye for an eye, and a tooth for a tooth. But I say unto

00:22:18.440 --> 00:22:25.940
you, that ye resist not evil, but whosoever shall smite thee on thy right cheek, turn to him the

00:22:25.940 --> 00:22:32.640
other also. And if any man will sue thee at the law, and take away thy coat, let him have thy

00:22:32.640 --> 00:22:38.940
cloak also. And whosoever shall compel thee to go a mile, go with him twain.

00:22:39.920 --> 00:22:46.200
Give to him that asketh thee, and from him that would borrow of thee turn not thou away.

00:22:48.100 --> 00:22:53.360
Ye have heard that it hath been said, thou shalt love thy neighbor, and hate thy enemy.

00:22:54.240 --> 00:23:00.860
But I say unto you, love your enemies, bless them that curse you, do good to them that hate you,

00:23:01.620 --> 00:23:08.100
and pray for them which despitefully use you, and persecute you, that ye may be the children

00:23:08.100 --> 00:23:14.200
of your Father which is in heaven. For he maketh his Son to rise on the evil and on the good,

00:23:14.600 --> 00:23:21.380
and sendeth rain on the just and on the unjust. For if ye love them which love you,

00:23:21.580 --> 00:23:28.020
what reward have ye? Do not even the publicans the same? And if ye salute your brethren only,

00:23:29.000 --> 00:23:36.080
what do ye more than others? Do not even the publicans so? Be ye therefore perfect,

00:23:36.080 --> 00:23:39.960
even as your Father which is in heaven is perfect.

00:23:55.280 --> 00:23:57.960
THIS LIBERVOX RECORDING IS IN THE PUBLIC DOMAIN.

00:24:01.100 --> 00:24:06.960
Take heed that ye do not your alms before men to be seen of them, otherwise ye have

00:24:06.960 --> 00:24:09.260
no reward of your Father which is in heaven.

00:24:10.520 --> 00:24:16.300
Therefore, when thou doest thine alms, do not sound a trumpet before thee as the hypocrites

00:24:16.300 --> 00:24:24.640
do in the synagogues and in the streets, that they may have glory of men, verily I say unto

00:24:24.640 --> 00:24:27.380
you, they have their reward.

00:24:28.560 --> 00:24:34.820
But when thou doest alms, let not thy left hand know what thy right hand doeth, that

00:24:34.820 --> 00:24:43.040
thine alms may be in secret, and thy Father which seeth in secret himself shall reward

00:24:43.040 --> 00:24:44.080
thee openly.

00:24:45.520 --> 00:24:52.140
And when thou prayest, thou shalt not be as the hypocrites are, for they love to pray

00:24:52.140 --> 00:24:58.180
standing in the synagogues and in the corners of the streets, that they may be seen of men,

00:24:59.240 --> 00:25:03.480
verily I say unto you, they have their reward.

00:25:05.220 --> 00:25:11.540
But when thou prayest, enter into thy closet, and when thou hast shut thy door, pray to

00:25:11.540 --> 00:25:19.300
thy Father which is in secret, and thy Father which seeth in secret shall reward thee openly.

00:25:20.500 --> 00:25:27.320
But when ye pray, use not vain repetitions as the heathen do, for they think that they

00:25:27.320 --> 00:25:29.400
shall be heard for their much speaking.

00:25:31.580 --> 00:25:37.960
Be not ye therefore like unto them, for your Father knoweth what things ye have need of

00:25:37.960 --> 00:25:39.420
before ye ask him.

00:25:39.720 --> 00:25:49.180
After this manner therefore pray ye, Our Father, which art in heaven, hallowed be thy name.

00:25:49.940 --> 00:25:54.660
Thy kingdom come, thy will be done in earth as it is in heaven.

00:25:55.680 --> 00:26:02.680
Give us this day our daily bread, and forgive us our debts as we forgive our debtors.

00:26:03.160 --> 00:26:08.480
And lead us not into temptation, but deliver us from evil.

00:26:09.280 --> 00:26:16.120
For thine is the kingdom, and the power, and the glory, for ever, amen.

00:26:18.040 --> 00:26:24.200
For if ye forgive men their trespasses, your heavenly Father will also forgive you.

00:26:24.400 --> 00:26:31.060
But if ye forgive not men their trespasses, neither will your Father forgive your trespasses.

00:26:31.060 --> 00:26:38.860
Moreover, when ye fast, be not as the hypocrites of a sad countenance, for they disfigure their

00:26:38.860 --> 00:26:43.280
faces that they may appear unto men to fast.

00:26:44.180 --> 00:26:47.940
Verily, I say unto you, they have their reward.

00:26:48.960 --> 00:26:55.180
But thou, when thou fastest, anoint thine head and wash thy face, that thou appear not

00:26:55.180 --> 00:26:59.760
unto men to fast, but unto thy Father which is in secret.

00:27:00.600 --> 00:27:05.1000
And thy Father, which seeth in secret, shall reward thee openly.

00:27:07.040 --> 00:27:13.140
Lay not up for yourselves treasures upon earth where moth and rust doth corrupt, and where

00:27:13.140 --> 00:27:15.380
thieves break through and steal.

00:27:16.120 --> 00:27:22.460
But lay up for yourselves treasures in heaven where neither moth nor rust doth corrupt,

00:27:22.860 --> 00:27:26.320
and where thieves do not break through nor steal.

00:27:27.080 --> 00:27:31.820
For where your treasure is, there will your heart be also.

00:27:33.960 --> 00:27:35.860
The light of the body is the eye.

00:27:36.640 --> 00:27:41.580
If therefore thine eye be single, thy whole body shall be full of light.

00:27:42.060 --> 00:27:46.640
But if thine eye be evil, thy whole body shall be full of darkness.

00:27:47.200 --> 00:27:50.440
If therefore the light that is in thee be darkness.

00:27:51.460 --> 00:27:53.120
How great is that darkness!

00:27:55.240 --> 00:27:57.380
No man can serve two masters.

00:27:58.400 --> 00:28:03.720
For either he will hate the one and love the other, or else he will hold to the one and

00:28:03.720 --> 00:28:04.980
despise the other.

00:28:05.740 --> 00:28:08.260
You cannot serve God and mammon.

00:28:10.340 --> 00:28:15.380
Therefore I say unto you, take no thought for your life, what ye shall eat, or what

00:28:15.380 --> 00:28:19.520
ye shall drink, nor yet for your body what ye shall put on.

00:28:20.200 --> 00:28:24.680
Is not the life more than meat, and the body than raiment?

00:28:25.960 --> 00:28:27.560
Behold the fowls of the air.

00:28:28.040 --> 00:28:33.380
For they sow not, neither do they reap, nor gather into barns, yet your heavenly fodder

00:28:33.380 --> 00:28:34.100
feedeth them.

00:28:34.580 --> 00:28:36.680
Are ye not much better than they?

00:28:37.220 --> 00:28:41.460
Which of you, by taking thought, can add one cubit unto a stature?

00:28:42.140 --> 00:28:44.400
And why take ye thought for raiment?

00:28:44.980 --> 00:28:50.460
Consider the lilies of the field, how they grow, they toil not, neither do they spin,

00:28:50.560 --> 00:28:56.580
and yet I say unto you, that even Solomon, in all his glory, was not arrayed like one

00:28:56.580 --> 00:28:57.320
of these.

00:28:58.620 --> 00:29:04.400
Wherefore if God so clothe the grass of the field, which today is and tomorrow is cast

00:29:04.400 --> 00:29:09.060
into the oven, shall he not much more clothe you, oh ye little faith?

00:29:10.100 --> 00:29:17.660
Therefore take no thought, saying, What shall we eat, or what shall we drink, or wherewith

00:29:17.660 --> 00:29:19.740
all shall we be clothed?

00:29:19.860 --> 00:29:22.840
For after all these things do the Gentiles seek.

00:29:23.420 --> 00:29:27.140
For your heavenly father knoweth that ye have need of all these things.

00:29:27.900 --> 00:29:35.260
But seek ye first the kingdom of God, and his righteousness, and all these things shall

00:29:35.260 --> 00:29:36.520
be added unto you.

00:29:36.520 --> 00:29:39.160
Take therefore no thought for the morrow.

00:29:39.740 --> 00:29:42.620
For the morrow shall take thought for the things of itself.

00:29:43.460 --> 00:29:46.820
Sufficient unto the day is the evil thereof.

00:30:06.735 --> 00:30:09.755
Judge not, that ye be not judged.

00:30:10.415 --> 00:30:13.895
For with what judgment ye judge, ye shall be judged.

00:30:14.695 --> 00:30:18.815
And with what measure ye meet, it shall be measured to you again.

00:30:19.335 --> 00:30:23.035
And why beholdest thou the mote that is in thy brother's eye?

00:30:23.035 --> 00:30:27.295
But considerest not the beam that is in thine own eye?

00:30:28.275 --> 00:30:32.775
How wilt thou say to thy brother, Let me pull out the mote out of thine eye?

00:30:32.955 --> 00:30:37.635
And behold, a beam is in thine own eye. Thou hypocrite!

00:30:38.295 --> 00:30:41.835
First cast out the beam out of thine own eye,

00:30:42.155 --> 00:30:46.315
and then thou shalt see clearly to cast out the mote out of thy brother's eye.

00:30:47.635 --> 00:30:53.015
Give not that which is holy unto the dogs. Neither cast ye your pearls before swine,

00:30:53.035 --> 00:30:57.575
lest they trample them under their feet, and turn again and rend you.

00:30:58.835 --> 00:31:04.075
Ask, and it shall be given you. Seek, and ye shall find.

00:31:05.335 --> 00:31:11.195
Knock, and it shall be opened unto you. For every one that asketh receiveth,

00:31:12.275 --> 00:31:18.315
and he that seeketh findeth. And to him that knocketh, it shall be opened.

00:31:18.315 --> 00:31:24.455
Or what man is there of you, whom, if his son ask bread, will give him a stone?

00:31:25.315 --> 00:31:32.775
Or if he ask a fish, will give him a serpent? If ye then being evil, know how to give good

00:31:32.775 --> 00:31:38.295
gifts unto your children? How much more shall your father which is in heaven,

00:31:38.715 --> 00:31:44.415
give good things to them that ask him? Therefore, all things whatsoever ye would

00:31:44.415 --> 00:31:52.375
that men should do to you, do ye even so to them. For this is the law, and the prophets.

00:31:53.375 --> 00:31:58.995
Enter ye at the straight gate, for wide is the gate, and broad is the way that leadeth to

00:31:58.995 --> 00:32:07.035
destruction, and many there be which go in thereat. But straight is the gate, and narrow is the way,

00:32:07.495 --> 00:32:10.755
which leadeth unto life, and few there be that find it.

00:32:12.275 --> 00:32:19.315
Beware of false prophets, which come to you in sheep's clothing, but inwardly they are

00:32:19.315 --> 00:32:27.915
ravening wolves. Ye shall know them by their fruits. Do men gather grapes of thorns, or figs

00:32:27.915 --> 00:32:36.435
of thistles? Even so, every good tree bringeth forth good fruit, but a corrupt tree bringeth

00:32:36.435 --> 00:32:44.695
evil fruit. A good tree cannot bring forth evil fruit, neither can a corrupt tree bring forth

00:32:44.695 --> 00:32:51.175
good fruit. Every tree that bringeth not forth good fruit is hewn down, and cast into the fire.

00:32:51.675 --> 00:33:00.135
Wherefore, by their fruits ye shall know them. Not every one that saith unto me, Lord, Lord,

00:33:00.695 --> 00:33:06.295
shall enter into the kingdom of heaven, but he that doeth the will of my father which is in heaven.

00:33:07.335 --> 00:33:15.495
Many will say to me in that day, Lord, Lord, have we not prophesied in thy name, and in thy name

00:33:15.495 --> 00:33:22.775
have cast out devils, and in thy name done many wonderful works? And then I will profess unto

00:33:22.775 --> 00:33:31.555
them, I never knew you, depart from me, ye that work iniquity. Therefore, whosoever heareth these

00:33:31.555 --> 00:33:38.955
sayings of mine and doeth them, I will liken him unto a wise man which built his house upon a rock.

00:33:40.335 --> 00:33:46.495
And the rain descended, and the floods came, and the winds blew, and beat upon that house,

00:33:46.515 --> 00:33:54.635
and it fell not, for it was founded upon a rock. And every one that heareth these sayings of mine

00:33:54.635 --> 00:34:01.875
and doeth them not shall be likened unto a foolish man which built his house upon the sand.

00:34:02.595 --> 00:34:07.735
And the rain descended, and the floods came, and the winds blew, and beat upon that house,

00:34:07.995 --> 00:34:11.755
and it fell, and great was the fall of it.

00:34:12.995 --> 00:34:18.975
And it came to pass, when Jesus had ended these sayings, the people were astonished at his

00:34:18.975 --> 00:34:24.495
doctrine, for he taught them as one having authority, and not as the scribes.

00:34:44.879 --> 00:34:51.559
When he was come down from the mountain great multitudes followed him, and, behold, there

00:34:51.559 --> 00:34:59.699
came a leper, and worshipped him, saying, Lord, if thou wilt, thou canst make me clean.

00:35:00.819 --> 00:35:09.199
And Jesus put forth his hand and touched him, saying, I will, be thou clean, and immediately

00:35:09.199 --> 00:35:11.759
his leprosy was cleansed.

00:35:12.579 --> 00:35:19.479
And Jesus saith unto him, See thou tell no man, but go thy way, show thyself to the

00:35:19.479 --> 00:35:24.339
priest, and offer the gift that Moses commanded for a testimony unto them.

00:35:25.039 --> 00:35:30.919
And when Jesus was entered into Capernaum, there came unto him a centurion beseeching

00:35:30.919 --> 00:35:38.819
him and saying, Lord, my servant lieth at home sick of the palsy, grievously tormented,

00:35:39.539 --> 00:35:43.699
and Jesus saith unto him, I will come and heal him.

00:35:44.959 --> 00:35:50.699
The centurion answered and said, Lord, I am not worthy that thou shouldest come under

00:35:50.699 --> 00:35:56.319
my roof, but speak the word only, and my servant shall be healed.

00:35:57.439 --> 00:36:04.679
For I am a man under authority, having soldiers under me, and I say to this man, Go, and he

00:36:04.679 --> 00:36:13.179
goeth, and to another, Come, and he cometh, and to my servant, Do this, and he doeth it.

00:36:14.099 --> 00:36:20.859
When Jesus heard it, he marveled, and said to them that followed, Verily, I say unto

00:36:20.859 --> 00:36:29.499
you, I have not found so great faith, no, not in Israel, and I say unto you, that many

00:36:29.499 --> 00:36:36.019
shall come from the east and the west, and shall sit down with Abraham and Isaac and

00:36:36.019 --> 00:36:43.159
Jacob in the kingdom of heaven, but the children of the kingdom shall be cast out into outer

00:36:43.159 --> 00:36:48.219
darkness, there shall be weeping and gnashing of teeth.

00:36:49.539 --> 00:36:57.699
And Jesus said unto the centurion, Go thy way, and as thou hast believed, so be it done

00:36:57.699 --> 00:37:02.859
unto thee, and his servant was healed in the self-same hour.

00:37:03.939 --> 00:37:10.639
And when Jesus was come into Peter's house, he saw his wife's mother laid and sick of

00:37:10.639 --> 00:37:19.539
fever, and he touched her hand, and the fever left her, and she arose and ministered unto

00:37:19.539 --> 00:37:20.299
them.

00:37:21.479 --> 00:37:27.959
When the even was come, they brought unto him many that were possessed with devils,

00:37:28.219 --> 00:37:35.819
and he cast out the spirits with his word, and healed all that were sick, that it might

00:37:35.819 --> 00:37:45.379
which was spoken by Isaiah the prophet, saying, himself took our infirmities, and bare our

00:37:46.419 --> 00:37:47.199
sicknesses.

00:37:47.199 --> 00:37:52.799
Now when Jesus saw great multitudes about him, he gave commandment to depart unto the

00:37:52.799 --> 00:37:53.759
other side.

00:37:55.339 --> 00:38:01.899
And a certain scribe came, and said unto him, Master, I will follow thee whithersoever thou

00:38:01.899 --> 00:38:02.499
goest.

00:38:03.399 --> 00:38:13.019
And Jesus saith unto him, The foxes have holes, and the birds of the air have nests, for the

00:38:13.019 --> 00:38:15.719
Son of Man hath not where to lay his head.

00:38:17.499 --> 00:38:24.019
And another of his disciples said unto him, Lord, suffer me first to go and bury my father.

00:38:25.019 --> 00:38:32.179
But Jesus said unto him, Follow me, and let the dead bury their dead.

00:38:33.919 --> 00:38:41.799
And when he was entered into a ship, his disciples followed him, and, behold, there arose a great

00:38:41.799 --> 00:38:47.219
tempest in the sea, insomuch that the ship was covered with the waves.

00:38:47.819 --> 00:38:54.659
But he was asleep, and his disciples came to him, and awoke him, saying, Lord, save us,

00:38:54.659 --> 00:38:55.579
we perish.

00:38:56.999 --> 00:39:03.099
And he said unto them, Why are ye fearful, O ye of little faith?

00:39:04.439 --> 00:39:11.619
And he arose, and rebuked the winds and the sea, and there was a great calm.

00:39:12.579 --> 00:39:19.859
But the men marveled, saying, What manner of man is this, that even the winds and the

00:39:19.859 --> 00:39:21.179
sea obey him?

00:39:22.119 --> 00:39:27.879
And when he was come to the other side, into the country of the Gyrgossines, there met

00:39:27.879 --> 00:39:34.779
him two possessed with devils, coming out of the tombs, exceeding phiris, so that no

00:39:34.779 --> 00:39:41.599
man might pass by that way, and, behold, they cried out, saying, What have we to do with

00:39:41.599 --> 00:39:44.399
thee, Jesus, thou son of God?

00:39:45.359 --> 00:39:49.119
Art thou come hither to torment us before the time?

00:39:49.939 --> 00:39:54.319
And there was a good way off from them, and heard of many swine feeding.

00:39:54.919 --> 00:40:02.099
So the devils besought him, saying, If thou cast us out, suffer us to go away into the

00:40:02.099 --> 00:40:03.479
herd of swine.

00:40:04.519 --> 00:40:06.419
And he said unto them, Go.

00:40:06.659 --> 00:40:11.499
And when they were come out, they went into the herd of swine.

00:40:11.719 --> 00:40:18.819
And behold, the whole herd of swine ran violently down a steep place into the sea, and perished

00:40:18.819 --> 00:40:19.719
in the waters.

00:40:20.599 --> 00:40:27.099
And they that kept them fled, and went their ways into the city, and told everything and

00:40:27.099 --> 00:40:29.939
what was befallen to the possessed of the devils.

00:40:30.599 --> 00:40:33.479
And behold, the whole city came out to meet Jesus.

00:40:34.539 --> 00:40:40.139
And when they saw him, they besought him, that he would depart out of their coasts.

00:40:49.267 --> 00:40:50.307
9.

00:41:00.167 --> 00:41:08.387
And he entered into a ship and passed over, and came into his own city, and, behold, they

00:41:08.387 --> 00:41:12.407
brought to him a man sick of the palsy, lying on a bed.

00:41:12.407 --> 00:41:16.647
10. And Jesus, seeing their faith, said unto the sick of the palsy,

00:41:17.087 --> 00:41:22.607
Son, be of good cheer, thy sins be forgiven thee.

00:41:22.807 --> 00:41:28.467
11. And, behold, certain of the scribes said within themselves, This man bless femeth.

00:41:29.307 --> 00:41:34.867
12. And Jesus, knowing their thoughts, said, Wherefore think ye evil in your hearts?

00:41:35.507 --> 00:41:42.427
13. For whether is easier to say, Thy sins be forgiven thee, or to say, Arise, and walk.

00:41:43.307 --> 00:41:48.227
14. But that ye may know that the Son of man hath power on earth to forgive sins,

00:41:48.947 --> 00:41:56.927
Then saith he to the sick of the palsy, Arise, take up thy bed, and go unto thine house.

00:41:57.227 --> 00:42:00.547
15. And he arose, and departed to his house.

00:42:01.487 --> 00:42:06.647
16. But when the multitude saw it, they marveled, and glorified God,

00:42:07.127 --> 00:42:13.167
which had given such power unto men. 17. And as Jesus passed forth from thence,

00:42:13.307 --> 00:42:17.647
he saw a man named Matthew, sitting at the receipt of custom.

00:42:18.227 --> 00:42:21.267
18. And he saith unto him, Follow me.

00:42:21.927 --> 00:42:28.047
19. And he arose, and followed him. And it came to pass, as Jesus sat at

00:42:28.047 --> 00:42:32.567
the receipt of custom. 20. And behold, many publicans and sinners came,

00:42:32.907 --> 00:42:38.867
and sat down with him and his disciples. 21. And when the Pharisees saw it,

00:42:39.667 --> 00:42:45.407
they said unto his disciples, Why eateth your master with publicans and sinners?

00:42:46.327 --> 00:42:52.787
22. But when Jesus heard that, he said unto them, They that behold need not a physician,

00:42:53.667 --> 00:42:59.987
but they that are sick, but go ye and learn what that meaneth, I will have mercy,

00:43:00.627 --> 00:43:07.927
and not sacrifice. For I am not come to call the righteous, but sinners to repentance.

00:43:09.287 --> 00:43:16.607
23. Then came to him the disciples of John, saying, Why do we and the Pharisees fast oft,

00:43:17.107 --> 00:43:21.807
but thy disciples fast not? And Jesus said unto them,

00:43:22.787 --> 00:43:27.927
Can the children of the bride-chamber mourn, as long as the bridegroom is with them?

00:43:28.907 --> 00:43:33.607
24. But the days will come, when the bridegroom shall be taken from them,

00:43:34.447 --> 00:43:40.747
and then shall they fast. 25. No man putteth a piece of new cloth

00:43:40.747 --> 00:43:46.667
unto an old garment, for that which is put in to fill it up taketh from the garment.

00:43:47.727 --> 00:43:51.007
26. And the rent is made worse, neither do men

00:43:51.007 --> 00:43:57.507
put new wine into old bottles, else the bottles break, and the wine runneth out,

00:43:57.567 --> 00:44:01.767
and the bottles perish. 27. But they put new wine

00:44:01.767 --> 00:44:10.107
into new bottles, and both are preserved. 28. While he spake these things unto them, behold,

00:44:10.727 --> 00:44:17.767
there came a certain ruler, and worshipped him, saying, My daughter is even now dead,

00:44:17.767 --> 00:44:22.127
but come, and lay thy hand upon her, and she shall live.

00:44:22.547 --> 00:44:28.667
29. And Jesus arose, and followed him, and so did his disciples. And behold, a woman,

00:44:29.027 --> 00:44:34.027
which was diseased, with an issue of blood twelve years, came behind him,

00:44:34.367 --> 00:44:39.327
and touched the hem of his garment. 30. For she said within herself,

00:44:39.987 --> 00:44:44.347
If I may but touch his garment, I shall be whole.

00:44:45.147 --> 00:44:53.027
But Jesus turned him about, and when he saw her, he said, Daughter, be of good comfort,

00:44:54.087 --> 00:45:00.247
thy faith has made thee whole. And the woman was made whole from that hour.

00:45:02.627 --> 00:45:09.607
And when Jesus came into the ruler's house, and saw the minstrels, and the people making a noise,

00:45:09.607 --> 00:45:19.707
he said unto them, Give place, for the maid is not dead, but sleepeth, and they laughed him to scorn.

00:45:21.627 --> 00:45:26.587
But when the people were put forth, he went in, and took her by the hand.

00:45:27.547 --> 00:45:34.087
And the maid arose, and the fame hereof went abroad into all that land.

00:45:35.907 --> 00:45:45.967
And when Jesus departed thence, two blind men followed him, crying, and saying, Thou son of David, have mercy on us.

00:45:47.487 --> 00:45:53.987
And when he was come into the house, the blind men came to him, and Jesus saith unto them,

00:45:54.927 --> 00:45:59.967
Believe ye that I am able to do this? They said unto him, Yea, Lord.

00:46:00.767 --> 00:46:07.187
Then touched he their eyes, saying, According to your faith, be it unto you.

00:46:07.667 --> 00:46:14.927
And their eyes were opened, and Jesus straightly charged them, saying, See that no man know it.

00:46:15.767 --> 00:46:20.887
But they, when they were departed, spread abroad his fame in all that country.

00:46:23.107 --> 00:46:28.867
As they went out, behold, they brought to him a dumb man possessed with a devil.

00:46:29.967 --> 00:46:33.887
And when the devil was cast out, the dumb spake.

00:46:35.427 --> 00:46:41.007
And the multitudes marveled, saying, It was never so seen in Israel.

00:46:42.427 --> 00:46:48.247
But the Pharisees said, He casteth out devils through the prince of the devils.

00:46:49.247 --> 00:46:54.307
And when Jesus went about all the cities and villages, teaching in their synagogues,

00:46:54.307 --> 00:47:01.287
preaching the gospel of the kingdom, and healing every sickness and every disease among the people.

00:47:01.987 --> 00:47:08.947
But when he saw the multitudes, he was moved with compassion on them, because they fainted,

00:47:09.107 --> 00:47:13.287
and were scattered abroad as sheep, having no shepherd.

00:47:13.827 --> 00:47:18.707
Then saith he unto his disciples, The harvest truly is plenteous.

00:47:19.867 --> 00:47:25.867
But the laborers are few. Pray ye therefore the Lord of the harvest,

00:47:26.467 --> 00:47:30.067
that he will send forth laborers into his harvest.

00:47:51.572 --> 00:47:54.332
And when he called unto him his twelve disciples

00:47:54.672 --> 00:48:02.872
He gave them power against unclean spirits to cast them out and to heal all manner of sickness and

00:48:03.632 --> 00:48:05.172
all manner of disease

00:48:05.692 --> 00:48:13.752
Now the names of the twelve Apostles are these the first Simon who was called Peter and Andrew his brother

00:48:13.752 --> 00:48:17.172
James the son of Zebedee and John his brother

00:48:17.752 --> 00:48:25.492
Philip and Bartholomew Thomas and Matthew the publican James the son of Alpheus in

00:48:25.492 --> 00:48:27.732
Labais whose surname was Thaddeus

00:48:28.792 --> 00:48:31.692
Simon the Canaanite and

00:48:31.692 --> 00:48:35.152
Judas Iscariot who also betrayed him

00:48:35.932 --> 00:48:41.232
These twelve Jesus sent forth and commanded them saying go not

00:48:41.232 --> 00:48:47.212
Into the way of the Gentiles and into any city of the Samaritans enter ye not

00:48:47.212 --> 00:48:52.472
but go rather to the lost sheep of the house of Israel and

00:48:52.472 --> 00:48:54.272
As ye go preach saying

00:48:54.272 --> 00:48:56.972
The kingdom of heaven is at hand

00:48:58.152 --> 00:49:05.152
Heal the sick cleanse the lepers raise the dead cast out devils

00:49:05.772 --> 00:49:07.792
freely ye have received

00:49:08.772 --> 00:49:10.392
freely give

00:49:11.512 --> 00:49:15.332
Provide neither gold nor silver nor brass in your purses

00:49:15.992 --> 00:49:18.072
nor script for your journey

00:49:18.072 --> 00:49:20.752
neither two coats neither shoes

00:49:20.752 --> 00:49:23.092
nor yet staves

00:49:23.092 --> 00:49:26.692
for the workmen is worthy of his meat and

00:49:26.692 --> 00:49:29.672
Into whatsoever city or town ye shall enter

00:49:30.572 --> 00:49:37.252
Inquire who in it is worthy and there abide till ye go thence and

00:49:37.252 --> 00:49:41.692
When ye come into an house salute it and if the house be worthy

00:49:42.452 --> 00:49:44.672
Let your peace come upon it

00:49:45.212 --> 00:49:50.252
but if it be not worthy let your peace return to you and

00:49:50.252 --> 00:49:57.512
Whosoever shall not receive you nor hear your words when ye depart out of that house or city

00:49:57.512 --> 00:50:00.112
Shake off the dust of your feet

00:50:01.792 --> 00:50:04.612
Verily I say unto you it

00:50:04.612 --> 00:50:11.852
Shall be more tolerable for the land of Sodom and Gomorrah in the day of judgment than for that city

00:50:13.172 --> 00:50:17.752
Behold I send you forth as sheep in the midst of wolves

00:50:18.292 --> 00:50:21.952
be ye therefore wise as serpents and

00:50:22.992 --> 00:50:24.672
harmless as doves

00:50:25.272 --> 00:50:27.092
But beware of men

00:50:27.512 --> 00:50:30.872
for they will deliver you up to the councils and

00:50:31.512 --> 00:50:37.632
They will scourge you in their synagogues and ye shall be brought before governors and

00:50:38.332 --> 00:50:40.012
Kings for my sake

00:50:40.012 --> 00:50:43.152
for a testimony against them in the Gentiles

00:50:44.352 --> 00:50:46.712
But when they deliver you up

00:50:46.712 --> 00:50:50.152
Take no thought how or what ye shall speak

00:50:50.152 --> 00:50:54.152
For it shall be given you in that same hour what ye shall speak

00:50:55.452 --> 00:51:04.332
For it is not ye that speak but the spirit of your father which speaketh in you and

00:51:04.332 --> 00:51:10.372
The brother shall deliver up the brother to death and the father the child and

00:51:10.372 --> 00:51:16.932
The children shall rise up against their parents and cause them to be put to death and

00:51:16.932 --> 00:51:20.392
Ye shall be hated of all men for my name's sake

00:51:21.072 --> 00:51:24.392
But he that endureth to the end shall be saved

00:51:25.412 --> 00:51:30.292
But when they persecute you in this city flee ye into another

00:51:30.292 --> 00:51:35.592
For verily I say unto you ye shall not have gone over the cities of Israel

00:51:36.112 --> 00:51:38.652
till the Son of Man become

00:51:40.012 --> 00:51:45.552
The disciple is not above his master nor the servant above his Lord

00:51:45.552 --> 00:51:52.292
It is enough for the disciple that he be as his master and

00:51:52.292 --> 00:51:54.272
the servant as his Lord

00:51:54.272 --> 00:51:58.732
If they have called the master of the house be Elzebub

00:51:59.432 --> 00:52:03.512
How much more shall they call them of his household?

00:52:04.432 --> 00:52:06.032
Fear them not therefore

00:52:06.712 --> 00:52:13.732
For there is nothing covered that shall not be revealed and hid that shall not be known

00:52:14.492 --> 00:52:16.922
What I tell you in darkness that

00:52:17.652 --> 00:52:19.682
speak ye in light and

00:52:20.192 --> 00:52:21.882
What ye hear in the ear?

00:52:22.912 --> 00:52:27.952
that preach ye upon the housetops and

00:52:27.952 --> 00:52:29.902
Fear not them which kill the body

00:52:30.372 --> 00:52:32.842
But are not able to kill the soul

00:52:33.092 --> 00:52:39.082
But rather fear him which is able to destroy both soul and body in hell

00:52:40.782 --> 00:52:44.522
Are not two sparrows sold for a farthing and

00:52:46.122 --> 00:52:48.482
One of them shall not fall on the ground

00:52:48.962 --> 00:52:50.522
without your father

00:52:50.522 --> 00:52:53.842
But the very hairs of your head are all numbered

00:52:54.962 --> 00:52:57.202
Fear ye not therefore

00:52:57.202 --> 00:53:01.122
Ye are of more value than many sparrows

00:53:03.642 --> 00:53:07.202
Whosoever therefore shall confess me before men

00:53:07.202 --> 00:53:11.982
Him will I confess also before my father which is in heaven

00:53:12.982 --> 00:53:16.602
But whosoever shall deny me before men

00:53:16.602 --> 00:53:21.762
Him will I also deny before my father which is in heaven

00:53:21.762 --> 00:53:28.562
Think not that I am come to send peace on earth. I came not to send peace

00:53:28.562 --> 00:53:30.402
but a sword

00:53:30.402 --> 00:53:38.562
For I am come to set a man at variance against his father and the daughter against her mother and

00:53:38.562 --> 00:53:40.022
the daughter-in-law

00:53:40.022 --> 00:53:45.942
Against her mother-in-law and a man's foes shall be they of his own household

00:53:47.062 --> 00:53:53.342
He that loveth father or mother more than me is not worthy of me and

00:53:53.342 --> 00:53:59.282
He that loveth son or daughter more than me is not worthy of me and

00:53:59.282 --> 00:54:06.112
He that taketh not his cross and followeth after me is not worthy of me

00:54:08.312 --> 00:54:17.112
He that findeth his life shall lose it and he that looseth his life for my sake shall find it

00:54:18.222 --> 00:54:26.752
He that receiveth you receiveth me and he that receiveth me receiveth him that sent me

00:54:28.332 --> 00:54:32.592
He that receiveth a prophet in the name of a prophet shall

00:54:32.592 --> 00:54:39.712
Receive a prophet's reward and he that receiveth a righteous man in the name of a righteous man shall

00:54:39.712 --> 00:54:42.072
Receive a righteous man's reward

00:54:43.592 --> 00:54:51.112
And whosoever shall give to drink unto one of these little ones a cup of cold water only

00:54:51.112 --> 00:54:53.072
In the name of a disciple

00:54:53.072 --> 00:54:56.732
Verily I say unto you he shall in no while

00:54:56.732 --> 00:54:58.392
Lose his reward

00:55:19.751 --> 00:55:26.791
And it came to pass, when Jesus had made an end of commanding his twelve disciples, he

00:55:26.791 --> 00:55:30.491
departed thence to teach, and to preach in their cities.

00:55:31.471 --> 00:55:38.071
Now when John had heard in the prison the works of Christ, he sent two of his disciples,

00:55:39.071 --> 00:55:44.711
and said unto him, Art thou he that should come, or do we look for another?

00:55:45.811 --> 00:55:53.331
Jesus answered and said unto them, Go, and show John again those things which ye do hear and see.

00:55:53.331 --> 00:56:01.571
The blind receive their sight, and the lame walk, the lepers are cleansed, and the deaf hear,

00:56:01.991 --> 00:56:07.491
the dead are raised up, and the poor have the gospel preached to them.

00:56:08.931 --> 00:56:13.271
And blessed is he whosoever shall not be offended in me.

00:56:14.711 --> 00:56:20.811
And as they departed, Jesus began to say unto the multitudes concerning John,

00:56:21.711 --> 00:56:28.031
What went ye out into the wilderness to see? A reed shaken with the wind?

00:56:29.091 --> 00:56:34.331
But what went ye out for to see? A man clothed in soft raiment?

00:56:34.971 --> 00:56:39.071
Behold, they that wear soft clothing are in kings' houses.

00:56:40.091 --> 00:56:46.791
But what went ye out for to see? A prophet? Yea, I say unto you, and more than a prophet.

00:56:47.511 --> 00:56:54.971
For this is he of whom it is written, Behold, I send my messenger before thy face,

00:56:55.911 --> 00:57:03.451
which shall prepare thy way before thee. Verily I say unto you, among them that are born of women,

00:57:03.731 --> 00:57:08.351
there hath not risen a greater than John the Baptist, notwithstanding,

00:57:08.791 --> 00:57:13.091
he that is least in the kingdom of heaven is greater than he.

00:57:14.031 --> 00:57:19.751
And from the days of John the Baptist until now the kingdom of heaven suffereth violence,

00:57:20.371 --> 00:57:27.851
and the violent take it by force. For all the prophets and the law prophesied until John.

00:57:28.711 --> 00:57:35.211
And if ye will receive it, this is Elias, which was for to come.

00:57:35.211 --> 00:57:43.791
He that hath ears to hear, let him hear. But whereunto shall I liken this generation?

00:57:45.071 --> 00:57:49.911
It is like unto children sitting in the markets, and calling unto their fellows,

00:57:50.071 --> 00:57:55.471
and saying, We have piped unto you, and ye have not danced,

00:57:56.071 --> 00:58:00.011
we have mourned unto you, and ye have not lamented.

00:58:00.891 --> 00:58:07.791
For John came neither eating nor drinking, and they say, He hath a devil.

00:58:09.571 --> 00:58:16.031
The Son of Man came eating and drinking, and they say, Behold, a man gluttonous,

00:58:16.551 --> 00:58:24.491
and a wine-bibber, a friend to publicans and sinners. But wisdom is justified of her children.

00:58:25.551 --> 00:58:30.991
Then began he to upbraid the cities wherein most of his mighty works were done,

00:58:31.371 --> 00:58:39.011
because they repented not. Woe unto thee, Chorazin! Woe unto thee, Bethsaida!

00:58:40.031 --> 00:58:44.891
For if the mighty works which were done in you had been done in Tyre and Sidon,

00:58:45.131 --> 00:58:49.151
they would have repented long ago in sackcloth and ashes.

00:58:49.971 --> 00:58:58.751
But I say unto you, It shall be more tolerable for Tyre and Sidon at the day of judgment than for you.

00:58:59.631 --> 00:59:06.571
And thou Capernaum, which art exalted unto heaven, shalt be brought down to hell.

00:59:06.831 --> 00:59:11.511
For if the mighty works which had been done in thee had been done in Sodom,

00:59:11.511 --> 00:59:16.091
it would have remained until this day. But I say unto you,

00:59:16.091 --> 00:59:23.191
that it shall be more tolerable for the land of Sodom in the day of judgment than for thee.

00:59:23.951 --> 00:59:30.431
At that time Jesus answered and said, I thank thee, O Father, Lord of heaven and earth,

00:59:31.311 --> 00:59:39.391
because thou hast hid these things from the wise and prudent, and hast revealed them unto babes.

00:59:39.411 --> 00:59:42.971
Even so, Father, for so it seemed good in thy sight.

00:59:43.671 --> 00:59:50.491
All things are delivered unto me of my Father, and no man knoweth the Son but the Father,

00:59:50.851 --> 00:59:57.251
neither knoweth any man the Father save the Son, and he to whomsoever the Son will reveal him.

00:59:57.911 --> 01:00:06.511
Come unto me, all ye that labor and are heavy laden, and I will give you rest,

01:00:06.511 --> 01:00:13.131
take my yoke upon you, and learn of me. For I am meek and lowly in heart,

01:00:13.791 --> 01:00:21.971
and ye shall find rest unto your souls. For my yoke is easy, and my burden is light.

01:00:43.025 --> 01:00:48.735
At that time Jesus went on the Sabbath day through the corn and his disciples

01:00:49.285 --> 01:00:54.505
Were and hungered and began to pluck the ears of corn and to eat

01:00:55.465 --> 01:01:00.405
But when the Pharisees saw it they said unto him behold thy disciples

01:01:00.405 --> 01:01:05.685
Do that which is not lawful to do upon the Sabbath day, but he said unto them

01:01:05.685 --> 01:01:12.085
Have you not read what David did when he was and hungered and they that were with him?

01:01:12.165 --> 01:01:19.785
How he entered into the house of God and did eat the showbread which was not lawful for him to eat neither for them

01:01:19.785 --> 01:01:22.605
That were with him, but only for the priests

01:01:23.385 --> 01:01:25.925
Or have you not read in the law?

01:01:26.545 --> 01:01:32.345
How that on the Sabbath days the priests in the temple profane the Sabbath and are blameless

01:01:32.345 --> 01:01:38.025
But I say unto you that in this place is one greater than the temple

01:01:38.025 --> 01:01:44.765
But if ye had known what this meaneth I will have mercy and not sacrifice

01:01:45.565 --> 01:01:48.365
Ye would have not condemned the guiltless

01:01:49.165 --> 01:01:52.585
For the Son of Man is Lord even of the Sabbath day

01:01:52.605 --> 01:01:55.505
And when he was departed thence

01:01:56.285 --> 01:02:04.145
He went into their synagogue and behold there was a man which had his hand withered and

01:02:04.145 --> 01:02:12.065
They asked him saying is it lawful to heal on the Sabbath days that they might accuse him and

01:02:12.065 --> 01:02:17.965
He said unto them what man shall there be among you that shall have one sheep and

01:02:18.485 --> 01:02:24.705
If it fall into a pit on the Sabbath day will he not lay hold on it and lift it out

01:02:25.285 --> 01:02:28.365
How much then is a man better than a sheep?

01:02:29.565 --> 01:02:33.085
Wherefore it is lawful to do well on the Sabbath days

01:02:34.245 --> 01:02:36.165
Then saith he to the man

01:02:36.845 --> 01:02:38.985
stretch forth thine hand and

01:02:39.665 --> 01:02:44.985
He stretched it forth and it was restored whole like as the other

01:02:44.985 --> 01:02:51.845
Then the Pharisees went out and held counsel against him how they might destroy him

01:02:52.845 --> 01:02:57.885
but when Jesus knew it he withdrew himself from thence and

01:02:57.885 --> 01:03:02.925
great multitudes followed him and he healed them all and

01:03:02.925 --> 01:03:10.965
Charged them that they should not make him known that it might be fulfilled which was spoken by Isaiah as the prophet saying

01:03:11.865 --> 01:03:15.405
Behold my servant whom I have chosen

01:03:15.405 --> 01:03:20.305
My beloved in whom my soul is well pleased

01:03:20.305 --> 01:03:25.965
I will put my spirit upon him and he shall show judgment to the Gentiles

01:03:26.965 --> 01:03:30.065
He shall not strive nor cry

01:03:30.065 --> 01:03:34.525
neither shall any man hear his voice in the streets a

01:03:34.525 --> 01:03:38.385
bruised reed shall he not break and

01:03:38.385 --> 01:03:46.745
Smoking flax shall he not quench till he send forth judgment unto victory and

01:03:46.745 --> 01:03:49.245
In his name shall the Gentiles trust

01:03:50.845 --> 01:03:58.585
Then was brought unto him one possessed with the devil blind and dumb and he healed him

01:03:59.225 --> 01:04:03.725
in so much that the blind and dumb both spake and saw and

01:04:04.665 --> 01:04:09.945
All the people were amazed and said is not this the son of David

01:04:10.645 --> 01:04:19.905
but when the Pharisees heard it they said this fellow doth not cast out devils but by Bielzebub the prince of the devils and

01:04:19.905 --> 01:04:22.885
Jesus knew their thoughts and said unto them

01:04:23.745 --> 01:04:29.565
every kingdom divided against itself is brought to desolation and

01:04:29.565 --> 01:04:35.625
Every city or house divided against itself shall not stand and

01:04:35.625 --> 01:04:38.085
if Satan cast out Satan

01:04:38.085 --> 01:04:44.225
He is divided against himself how shall then his kingdom stand and

01:04:45.045 --> 01:04:51.305
If I by Bielzebub cast out devils by whom do your children cast them out?

01:04:52.665 --> 01:04:54.885
Therefore they shall be your judges

01:04:54.885 --> 01:04:58.745
But if I cast out devils by the Spirit of God

01:04:58.745 --> 01:05:03.565
Then the kingdom of God is come unto you or else

01:05:03.565 --> 01:05:09.325
How can one enter into a strong man's house and spoil his goods except he first

01:05:09.745 --> 01:05:14.045
Bind the strong man and then he will spoil his house

01:05:14.845 --> 01:05:17.685
He that is not with me is

01:05:17.685 --> 01:05:20.025
against me and

01:05:20.025 --> 01:05:22.205
He that gathereth not with me

01:05:22.765 --> 01:05:24.085
scattereth abroad

01:05:25.685 --> 01:05:33.085
Wherefore I say unto you all manner of sin and blasphemy shall be forgiven unto men

01:05:33.605 --> 01:05:37.405
but the blasphemy against the Holy Ghost

01:05:37.405 --> 01:05:41.085
shall not be forgiven unto men and

01:05:41.085 --> 01:05:45.605
Whosoever speaketh the word against the son of man it shall be forgiven him

01:05:45.605 --> 01:05:49.105
But whosoever speaketh against the Holy Ghost

01:05:49.105 --> 01:05:54.705
It shall not be forgiven him neither in this world nor in the world to come

01:05:56.685 --> 01:06:00.205
Either make the tree good and

01:06:00.205 --> 01:06:01.805
his fruit good or

01:06:02.465 --> 01:06:10.805
Else make the tree corrupt and his fruit corrupt for the tree is known by his fruit. Oh

01:06:10.805 --> 01:06:15.925
Generation of vipers how can ye being evil speak good things?

01:06:16.885 --> 01:06:22.425
For out of the abundance of the heart the mouth speaketh a

01:06:22.425 --> 01:06:29.205
Good-man out of the good treasure of the heart bringeth forth good things and an evil man

01:06:29.585 --> 01:06:33.185
Out of the evil treasure bringeth forth evil things

01:06:33.185 --> 01:06:38.405
But I say unto you that every idle word that men shall speak

01:06:38.405 --> 01:06:41.485
They shall give account thereof in the day of judgment

01:06:42.245 --> 01:06:46.265
for by thy words thou shalt be justified and

01:06:47.305 --> 01:06:50.025
By thy words thou shalt be condemned

01:06:50.025 --> 01:06:57.985
Then certain of the scribes and of the Pharisees answered saying master we would see a sign from thee

01:06:58.985 --> 01:07:03.285
But he answered and said unto them an

01:07:03.285 --> 01:07:04.645
evil and adulterous

01:07:04.645 --> 01:07:10.235
Generation seeketh after a sign and there shall no sign be given to it

01:07:10.965 --> 01:07:13.105
but the sign of the prophet Jonas

01:07:13.945 --> 01:07:18.785
For as Jonas was three days and three nights in the whale's belly

01:07:18.785 --> 01:07:24.365
So shall the son of man be three days and three nights in the heart of the earth

01:07:25.385 --> 01:07:31.665
The men of Nineveh shall rise in judgment with this generation and shall condemn it

01:07:31.985 --> 01:07:39.325
Because they repented at the preaching of Jonas and behold a greater than Jonas is here

01:07:40.225 --> 01:07:47.025
The queen of the south shall rise up in the judgment with this generation and shall condemn it

01:07:47.585 --> 01:07:54.465
For she came from the uttermost parts of the earth to hear the wisdom of Solomon and behold a

01:07:54.805 --> 01:08:00.225
Greater than Solomon is here when the unclean spirit is gone out of a man

01:08:00.225 --> 01:08:04.145
He walketh through dry places seeking rest and findeth none

01:08:04.145 --> 01:08:10.405
Then he saith I will return into my house from whence I came out and

01:08:10.405 --> 01:08:14.645
When he has come he findeth it empty swept and garnished

01:08:14.645 --> 01:08:17.645
Then goeth he and taketh with himself

01:08:18.045 --> 01:08:25.085
Seven other spirits more wicked than himself and they enter in and dwell there and

01:08:25.085 --> 01:08:31.565
The last state of that man is worse than the first even so shall it be also unto this wicked generation

01:08:32.625 --> 01:08:34.985
While he yet talked to the people

01:08:35.765 --> 01:08:38.825
Behold his mother and his brethren stood without

01:08:39.505 --> 01:08:41.725
Desiring to speak with him

01:08:41.725 --> 01:08:48.725
Then one said unto him behold thy mother and thy brethren stand without desiring to speak with thee

01:08:49.405 --> 01:08:53.225
But he answered and said unto him that told him

01:08:53.945 --> 01:08:57.845
who is my mother and who are my brethren and

01:08:58.705 --> 01:09:05.525
He stretched forth his hand toward his disciples and said behold my mother and my brethren

01:09:06.205 --> 01:09:10.765
For whosoever shall do the will of my father which is in heaven

01:09:10.765 --> 01:09:17.025
The same is my brother and sister and mother

01:09:36.602 --> 01:09:43.262
The same day went Jesus out of the house, and sat by the seaside, and great multitudes

01:09:43.262 --> 01:09:49.842
were gathered together unto him, so that he went into a ship and sat, and the whole multitude

01:09:51.242 --> 01:09:59.782
and he spake many things unto them in parables, saying, Behold a sower went forth to sow,

01:10:00.462 --> 01:10:09.542
and when he sowed some seeds fell by the wayside, and the fowls came and devoured them up. Some

01:10:09.542 --> 01:10:16.202
fell upon stony places, where they had not much earth, and forthwith they sprung up,

01:10:16.202 --> 01:10:23.922
because they had no deepness of earth, and when the sun was up they were scorched, and because

01:10:23.922 --> 01:10:31.802
they had no root they withered away. And some fell among thorns, and the thorns sprung up and

01:10:31.802 --> 01:10:41.882
choked them. But other fell into good ground, and brought forth fruit, some and hundredfold,

01:10:41.882 --> 01:10:51.082
some sixtyfold, some thirtyfold. Who hath ears to hear? Let him hear. And the disciples came,

01:10:51.182 --> 01:10:58.402
and said unto him, Why speakest thou unto them in parables? He answered, and said unto them,

01:10:59.102 --> 01:11:05.222
Because it is given unto you to know the mysteries of the kingdom of heaven, but to them it is not

01:11:05.222 --> 01:11:14.542
given. For whosoever hath to him shall be given, and he shall have more abundance. But whosoever

01:11:14.542 --> 01:11:23.702
hath not, from him shall be taken away even that he hath. Therefore I speak to them in parables,

01:11:24.522 --> 01:11:33.662
because they seeing see not, and hearing they hear not, neither do they understand. And in

01:11:33.662 --> 01:11:41.922
them is fulfilled the prophecy of Isaiah, which saith, By hearing ye shall hear, and shall not

01:11:41.922 --> 01:11:51.582
understand, and seeing ye shall see, and shall not perceive. For this people's heart is waxed

01:11:51.582 --> 01:12:00.302
gross, and their ears are dull of hearing, and their eyes they have closed. Lest at any time they

01:12:00.302 --> 01:12:06.882
should see with their eyes, and hear with their ears, and should understand with their heart,

01:12:07.722 --> 01:12:16.462
and should be converted, and I should heal them. But blessed are your eyes, for they see, and your

01:12:16.462 --> 01:12:23.922
ears for they hear. For verily I say unto you, that many prophets and righteous men have desired

01:12:23.922 --> 01:12:31.262
to see those things which ye see, and have not seen them, and to hear those things which ye hear,

01:12:31.942 --> 01:12:39.242
and have not heard them. Hear ye therefore the parable of the sower. When anyone heareth the

01:12:39.242 --> 01:12:46.502
word of the kingdom, and understandeth it not, then cometh the wicked one, and catcheth away that

01:12:46.502 --> 01:12:54.402
which was sown in his heart. This is he which received seed by the wayside. But he that received

01:12:54.402 --> 01:13:01.942
the seed into stony places, the same is he that heareth the word, and anon with joy receiveth it.

01:13:02.402 --> 01:13:09.922
Yet hath he not root in himself, but dureth for a while. For when tribulation and persecution

01:13:09.922 --> 01:13:18.862
arises because of the word, by and by he is offended. He also that received seed among the

01:13:18.862 --> 01:13:26.482
thorns is he that heareth the word, and the care of this world, and the deceitfulness of riches,

01:13:27.382 --> 01:13:35.802
choke the word, and he becometh unfruitful. But he that received seed into the good ground is he

01:13:35.802 --> 01:13:42.542
that heareth the word, and understandeth it, which also beareth fruit, and bringeth forth,

01:13:42.902 --> 01:13:51.502
some an hundredfold, some sixty, some thirty. Another parable put he forth unto them, saying,

01:13:51.842 --> 01:13:59.802
The kingdom of heaven is likened unto a man which sowed good seed in his field. But while men slept,

01:13:59.802 --> 01:14:08.902
his enemy came, and sowed tares among the wheat, and went his way. But when the blade was sprung up,

01:14:09.242 --> 01:14:16.042
and brought forth fruit, then appeared the tares also. So the servants of the householder came,

01:14:16.162 --> 01:14:23.762
and said unto him, Sir, didst not thou sow good seed in thy field? From whence then hath it tares?

01:14:24.642 --> 01:14:32.342
He said unto them, An enemy hath done this. The servant said unto him, Wilt thou then that we go

01:14:32.342 --> 01:14:39.982
and gather them up? But he said, Nay, lest while ye gather up the tares ye root up also the wheat

01:14:39.982 --> 01:14:47.222
with them. Let both grow together until the harvest. And in the time of harvest I will say

01:14:47.222 --> 01:14:52.962
to the reapers, Gather ye together first the tares, and bind them in bundles to burn them.

01:14:52.962 --> 01:15:00.522
But gather the wheat into my barn. Another parable put he forth unto them, saying,

01:15:01.002 --> 01:15:07.222
The kingdom of heaven is likened to a grain of mustard seed, which a man took and sowed in his

01:15:07.222 --> 01:15:15.202
field, which indeed is the least of all seeds. But when it is grown, it is the greatest among

01:15:15.202 --> 01:15:23.482
herbs, and becometh a tree, so that the birds of the air come and lodge in the branches thereof.

01:15:24.922 --> 01:15:30.502
Another parable spake he unto them, The kingdom of heaven is like unto leaven,

01:15:31.062 --> 01:15:37.982
which a woman took and hid in three measures of meal, till the whole was leavened. All these

01:15:37.982 --> 01:15:44.722
things spake Jesus unto the multitude in parables. And without a parable spake he not unto them.

01:15:45.442 --> 01:15:52.742
It might be fulfilled which was spoken by the prophet, saying, I will open my mouth in parables.

01:15:53.642 --> 01:15:59.062
I will utter things which have been kept secret from the foundation of the world.

01:16:01.122 --> 01:16:08.682
Then Jesus sent the multitude away, and went into the house. And his disciples came unto him,

01:16:08.682 --> 01:16:15.682
saying, Declare unto us the parable of the tares of the field. He answered and said unto them,

01:16:16.102 --> 01:16:23.882
He that soweth the good seed is the Son of man, the field is the world, the good seed are the

01:16:23.882 --> 01:16:30.902
children of the kingdom, but the tares are the children of the wicked one. The enemy that sowed

01:16:30.902 --> 01:16:37.602
them is the devil, the harvest is the end of the world, and the reapers are the angels.

01:16:38.582 --> 01:16:45.262
As therefore the tares are gathered and burned in the fire, so shall it be in the end of this

01:16:45.262 --> 01:16:53.662
world. The Son of man shall send forth his angels, and they shall gather out of his kingdom all

01:16:54.082 --> 01:17:01.162
things that offend, and them which do iniquity, and shall cast them into a furnace of fire.

01:17:01.162 --> 01:17:09.042
There shall be wailing and gnashing of teeth, then shall the righteous shine forth as the

01:17:09.042 --> 01:17:17.402
Son in the kingdom of their Father, who hath ears to hear let him hear. Again the kingdom of heaven

01:17:17.402 --> 01:17:27.592
is like unto treasure hidden in a field, the which when a man hath found he hideth, and for

01:17:27.592 --> 01:17:36.232
thereof goeth and selleth all that he hath, and buyeth that field. Again the kingdom of heaven is

01:17:36.232 --> 01:17:44.472
like unto a merchant man seeking goodly pearls, who when he had found one pearl of great price,

01:17:45.652 --> 01:17:56.292
went and sold all that he had, and bought it. Again the kingdom of heaven is like unto a net

01:17:56.292 --> 01:18:04.812
that was cast into the sea, and gathered of every kind, which when it was full they drew it to shore,

01:18:05.352 --> 01:18:13.952
and sat down, and gathered the good into vessels, but cast the bad away. So shall it be at the end

01:18:13.952 --> 01:18:23.652
of the world. The angel shall come forth, and sever the wicked from among the just, and shall

01:18:23.652 --> 01:18:29.552
cast them into the furnace of fire. There shall be wailing and gnashing of teeth.

01:18:31.832 --> 01:18:39.352
Jesus saith unto them, Have ye understood all these things? They say unto him, Yea, Lord.

01:18:40.332 --> 01:18:46.912
Then said he unto them, Therefore every scribe which is instructed unto the kingdom of heaven,

01:18:47.532 --> 01:18:53.632
is like unto a man that is an householder, which bringeth forth out of his treasure things new,

01:18:53.632 --> 01:19:01.532
and old. And it came to pass that when Jesus had finished these parables, he departed thence,

01:19:02.692 --> 01:19:08.832
and when he was come into his own country, he taught them in their synagogue, in so much

01:19:08.832 --> 01:19:16.372
that they were astonished, and said, Whence hath this man this wisdom, and these mighty works?

01:19:17.512 --> 01:19:25.832
Is not this the carpenter's son? Is not his mother called Mary, and his brethren James,

01:19:26.052 --> 01:19:36.272
and Joses, and Simon, and Judas, and his sisters? Are they not all with us? Whence then hath this

01:19:36.272 --> 01:19:45.972
man all these things? And they were offended in him. But Jesus said unto them, A prophet is not

01:19:45.972 --> 01:19:55.692
without honor save in his own country, and in his own house. And he did not many mighty works

01:19:55.692 --> 01:20:02.312
there because of their unbelief.

01:20:19.359 --> 01:20:26.919
At that time Herod the Tetrarch heard of the fame of Jesus, and said unto his servants,

01:20:27.179 --> 01:20:33.279
This is John the Baptist, he is risen from the dead, and therefore mighty works do show

01:20:33.279 --> 01:20:34.899
forth themselves in him.

01:20:34.899 --> 01:20:42.539
For Herod had laid hold on John, and bound him, and put him in prison for Herodias' sake,

01:20:42.679 --> 01:20:49.579
his brother Philip's wife. For John said unto him, It is not lawful for thee to have her.

01:20:50.379 --> 01:20:56.159
And when he would have put him to death, he feared the multitude, because they counted him as a

01:20:56.159 --> 01:21:03.919
prophet. But when Herod's birthday was kept, the daughter of Herodias danced before them,

01:21:03.919 --> 01:21:11.459
and pleased Herod, whereupon he promised with an oath to give her whatsoever she would ask.

01:21:12.839 --> 01:21:20.819
And she, being before instructed of her mother, said, Give me here John Baptist's head in a

01:21:20.819 --> 01:21:29.919
charger. And the king was sorry. Nevertheless, for the oath's sake, and them which sat with him at

01:21:29.919 --> 01:21:36.659
meet, he commanded it to be given to her. And he sent and beheaded John in the prison.

01:21:38.259 --> 01:21:45.819
And his head was brought in a charger, and given to the damsel, and she brought it to her mother.

01:21:46.739 --> 01:21:53.359
And his disciples came, and took up the body, and buried it, and went and told Jesus.

01:21:54.839 --> 01:22:03.719
When Jesus heard of it, he departed thence by ship into a desert place apart. And when the

01:22:03.719 --> 01:22:10.419
people had heard thereof, they followed him on foot out of the cities. And Jesus went forth,

01:22:10.879 --> 01:22:18.059
and saw a great multitude, and was moved with compassion toward them. And he healed their sick.

01:22:18.059 --> 01:22:25.699
And when it was evening, his disciples came to him, saying, This is a desert place, and the time

01:22:25.699 --> 01:22:32.179
is now past. Send the multitude away, that they may go into the villages, and buy themselves

01:22:33.399 --> 01:22:43.099
victuals. But Jesus said unto them, They need not depart. Give ye them to eat. And they say unto

01:22:43.959 --> 01:22:52.079
we have here but five loaves, and two fishes. He said, Bring them hither to me. And he commanded

01:22:52.079 --> 01:22:59.379
the multitude to sit down on the grass, and took the five loaves, and the two fishes. And looking

01:22:59.379 --> 01:23:07.539
up to heaven, he blessed, and break, and gave the loaves to his disciples, and the disciples to the

01:23:07.539 --> 01:23:16.199
multitude. And they did all eat, and were filled, and they took up of the fragments that remained

01:23:16.199 --> 01:23:24.459
twelve baskets full. And they that had eaten were about five thousand men besides women and children.

01:23:25.379 --> 01:23:32.779
And straightway Jesus constrained his disciples to get into a ship, and to go before him unto the

01:23:32.779 --> 01:23:41.539
side, while he sent the multitudes away. And when he had sent the multitudes away, he went up into a

01:23:41.539 --> 01:23:50.239
mountain apart to pray. And when the evening was come, he was there alone. But the ship was now in

01:23:50.239 --> 01:23:58.059
the midst of the sea, tossed with waves, for the wind was contrary. And in the fourth watch of the

01:23:58.059 --> 01:24:06.499
night, Jesus went unto them, walking on the sea. And when the disciples saw him walking on the sea,

01:24:06.759 --> 01:24:14.559
they were troubled, saying, It is a spirit. And they cried out for fear. But straightway Jesus

01:24:14.559 --> 01:24:22.479
spake unto them, saying, Be of good cheer at his eye, be not afraid. And Peter answered him, and said,

01:24:22.479 --> 01:24:34.619
Lord, if it be thou, bid me come unto thee on the water. And he said, Come. And when Peter was come

01:24:34.619 --> 01:24:43.079
down out of the ship, he walked on the water to go to Jesus. But when he saw the wind boisterous,

01:24:44.079 --> 01:24:53.459
he was afraid, and beginning to sink, he cried, saying, Lord, save me. And immediately Jesus

01:24:53.459 --> 01:25:00.359
stretched forth his hand, and caught him, and said unto him, O thou of little faith,

01:25:01.279 --> 01:25:07.639
wherefore didst thou doubt? And when they were come into the ship, the wind ceased.

01:25:09.259 --> 01:25:19.319
Then they that were in the ship came, and worshiped him, saying, Of a truth, thou art the Son of God.

01:25:20.299 --> 01:25:28.919
And when they were gone over, they came into the land of Gennesaret. And when the men of that place

01:25:28.919 --> 01:25:36.339
had knowledge of him, they sent out into all the country round about, and brought unto him all that

01:25:36.339 --> 01:25:44.379
were diseased, and besought him, that they might only touch the hem of his garment, and as many

01:25:44.379 --> 01:25:50.139
as touched were made perfectly whole

01:26:09.739 --> 01:26:15.979
Then came to Jesus scribes and Pharisees, which were of Jerusalem, saying,

01:26:16.299 --> 01:26:20.339
Why do thy disciples transgress the tradition of the elders?

01:26:21.519 --> 01:26:24.519
For they wash not their hands when they eat bread.

01:26:24.519 --> 01:26:27.459
But he answered and said unto them,

01:26:28.579 --> 01:26:32.839
Why do ye also transgress the commandment of God by your tradition?

01:26:33.579 --> 01:26:37.359
For God commanded, saying, Honor thy father and mother,

01:26:37.859 --> 01:26:42.319
And he that curseth father or mother, let him die the death.

01:26:42.939 --> 01:26:48.079
But ye say, Whosoever shall say to his father or his mother,

01:26:48.619 --> 01:26:52.819
It is a gift by whatsoever thou mightest be profited by me,

01:26:52.819 --> 01:26:57.399
And honor not his father or his mother, he shall be free.

01:26:58.359 --> 01:27:05.559
Thus have ye made the commandment of God of none effect by your tradition, ye hypocrites.

01:27:06.359 --> 01:27:13.019
Well did Esaias prophesy of you, saying, These people draweth nigh unto me with their mouth,

01:27:13.839 --> 01:27:18.999
And honoreth me with their lips, But their heart is far from me.

01:27:19.959 --> 01:27:26.479
But in vain they do worship me, Teaching for doctrines the commandments of men.

01:27:27.499 --> 01:27:33.039
And he called the multitude, And said unto them, Hear and understand.

01:27:34.719 --> 01:27:38.479
Not that which goeth into the mouth defileth a man,

01:27:39.119 --> 01:27:44.099
But that which cometh out of the mouth this defileth a man.

01:27:45.059 --> 01:27:48.319
Then came his disciples, And said unto him,

01:27:48.699 --> 01:27:52.419
Knowest thou that the Pharisees were offended when they heard this saying?

01:27:52.939 --> 01:27:59.279
But he answered and said, Every plant which my heavenly father hath not planted

01:27:59.279 --> 01:28:05.379
Shall be rooted up. Let them alone. They be blind leaders of the blind.

01:28:06.059 --> 01:28:11.659
And if the blind lead the blind, Both shall fall into the ditch.

01:28:11.659 --> 01:28:18.019
Then answered Peter and said unto him, Declare unto us this parable.

01:28:19.139 --> 01:28:23.999
And Jesus said, Are ye also yet without understanding?

01:28:24.859 --> 01:28:30.139
Do not ye yet understand, That whatsoever entereth in at the mouth

01:28:30.139 --> 01:28:34.899
Goeth into the belly, And is cast out into the draft?

01:28:35.459 --> 01:28:40.539
But those things which proceed out of the mouth Come forth from the heart,

01:28:40.539 --> 01:28:47.039
And they defile the man. For out of the heart proceed evil thoughts,

01:28:47.399 --> 01:28:53.839
Murders, adulteries, fornications, thefts, False witness, blasphemies.

01:28:54.319 --> 01:29:02.619
These are the things which defile a man. But to eat with unwashed hands defileth not a man.

01:29:03.559 --> 01:29:10.359
Then Jesus went thence, And departed into the coasts of Tyre and Sidon.

01:29:10.599 --> 01:29:14.779
And behold, a woman of Canaan came out of the same coasts,

01:29:15.679 --> 01:29:21.519
And cried unto him, saying, Have mercy on me, O Lord, thou son of David.

01:29:22.019 --> 01:29:28.779
My daughter is grievously vexed with a devil. But he answered her not a word.

01:29:28.779 --> 01:29:35.239
And his disciples came and besought him, saying, Send her away, for she crieth after us.

01:29:36.039 --> 01:29:42.819
But he answered and said, I am not sent, But unto the lost sheep of the house of Israel.

01:29:44.679 --> 01:29:49.679
Then came she and worshipped him, saying, Lord, help me.

01:29:51.659 --> 01:29:57.859
But he answered and said, It is not meat to take the children's bread,

01:29:57.859 --> 01:30:03.059
And to cast it to dogs. And she said, Truth, Lord,

01:30:03.379 --> 01:30:08.419
Yet the dogs eat of the crumbs which fall from their master's table.

01:30:10.059 --> 01:30:16.119
Then Jesus answered and said unto her, O woman, Great is thy faith.

01:30:17.259 --> 01:30:24.319
Be it unto thee even as thou wilt. And her daughter was made whole from that very hour.

01:30:25.839 --> 01:30:31.919
And Jesus departed from thence, And came nigh unto the sea of Galilee,

01:30:32.439 --> 01:30:38.999
And went up into a mountain and sat down there. And great multitudes came unto him,

01:30:39.259 --> 01:30:46.399
Having with them those that were lame, blind, dumb, maimed, and many others,

01:30:47.099 --> 01:30:52.659
And cast them down at Jesus' feet. And he healed them,

01:30:52.659 --> 01:31:00.239
In so much that the multitude wondered when they saw the dumb to speak, the maimed to be whole,

01:31:00.679 --> 01:31:07.399
The lame to walk, and the blind to see, And they glorified the God of Israel.

01:31:08.559 --> 01:31:16.219
Then Jesus called his disciples unto him, And said, I have compassion on the multitude,

01:31:16.739 --> 01:31:21.859
Because they continue with me now three days, And have nothing to eat.

01:31:22.659 --> 01:31:26.939
And I will not send them away fasting, lest they faint in the way.

01:31:28.519 --> 01:31:33.739
And his disciples say unto him, Whence should we have so much bread in the wilderness,

01:31:34.159 --> 01:31:41.719
As to fill so great a multitude? And Jesus saith unto them, How many loaves have ye?

01:31:42.219 --> 01:31:47.879
And they said, Seven, and a few fish. And he commanded the multitude to sit down on the ground.

01:31:48.789 --> 01:31:55.159
And he took the seven loaves and the fishes, And gave thanks and break them,

01:31:55.859 --> 01:32:03.439
And gave to his disciples and the disciples to the multitude. And they did all eat and were filled,

01:32:03.879 --> 01:32:11.559
And they took up of the broken meat that was left seven baskets full. And they that did eat

01:32:11.559 --> 01:32:17.639
Were four thousand men beside women and children. And he sent away the multitude,

01:32:18.499 --> 01:32:22.359
And took ship, and came into the coasts of Magdala.

01:32:43.500 --> 01:32:51.660
The Pharisees also, with the Sadducees, came, and, tempting, desired him that he would show them a sign from heaven.

01:32:52.660 --> 01:33:00.440
He answered and said unto them, When it is evening, ye say, It will be fair weather, for the sky is red.

01:33:01.040 --> 01:33:07.500
And in the morning, it will be foul weather today, for the sky is red and lowering.

01:33:08.520 --> 01:33:15.740
O ye hypocrites, ye can discern the face of the sky, but can ye not discern the signs of the times?

01:33:16.380 --> 01:33:29.360
A wicked and adulterous generation seeketh after a sign, and there shall no sign be given unto it, but the sign of the prophet Jonas, and he left them and departed.

01:33:29.960 --> 01:33:36.120
And when his disciples were come to the other side, they had forgotten to take bread.

01:33:37.200 --> 01:33:46.100
Then Jesus said unto them, Take heed, and beware of the leaven of the Pharisees and of the Sadducees.

01:33:46.540 --> 01:33:51.220
And they reasoned among themselves, saying, It is because we have taken no bread.

01:33:51.740 --> 01:34:02.580
Which when Jesus perceived, he said unto them, O ye of little faith, why reason ye among yourselves, because ye have brought no bread?

01:34:02.980 --> 01:34:11.780
Do ye not yet understand, neither remember the five loaves of the five thousand, and how many baskets ye took up?

01:34:12.400 --> 01:34:18.140
Neither the seven loaves of the four thousand, and how many baskets ye took up?

01:34:18.140 --> 01:34:30.320
How is it that ye do not understand that I spake it not to you concerning bread, that ye should beware of the leaven of the Pharisees and of the Sadducees?

01:34:30.640 --> 01:34:40.580
Then understood they how he bade them not to beware of the leaven of bread, but of the doctrine of the Pharisees and of the Sadducees.

01:34:40.580 --> 01:34:51.680
When Jesus came into the coasts of Caesarea Philippi, he asked his disciples, saying, Whom do men say that I, the Son of Man, am?

01:34:52.000 --> 01:35:00.620
And they said, Some say that thou art John the Baptist, some Elias, and others, Jeremiah, or one of the prophets.

01:35:01.400 --> 01:35:05.920
He sayeth unto them, But whom say ye that I am?

01:35:07.060 --> 01:35:15.360
And Simon Peter answered, and said, Thou art the Christ, the Son of the living God.

01:35:16.480 --> 01:35:30.520
And Jesus answered, and said unto him, Blessed art thou Simon Bar-Jonah, for flesh and blood hath not revealed it unto thee, but my Father which is in heaven.

01:35:31.920 --> 01:35:46.360
And I say also unto thee, That thou art Peter, and upon this rock I will build my church, and the gates of hell shall not prevail against it.

01:35:47.480 --> 01:36:02.800
And I will give unto thee the keys of the kingdom of heaven, and whatsoever thou shalt bind on earth shall be bound in heaven, and whatsoever thou shalt loose on earth shall be loosed in heaven.

01:36:03.600 --> 01:36:11.100
Then charged he his disciples, that they should tell no man that he was Jesus the Christ.

01:36:11.100 --> 01:36:29.980
From that time forth began Jesus to show unto his disciples how that he must go unto Jerusalem, and suffer many things of the elders and chief priests and scribes, and be killed, and be raised again the third day.

01:36:29.980 --> 01:36:39.080
Then Peter took him, and began to rebuke him, saying, Be it far from thee, Lord. This shall not be unto thee.

01:36:39.360 --> 01:36:56.160
But he turned, and said unto Peter, Get thee behind me, Satan. Thou art an offence unto me, for thou savourest not the things that be of God, but those that be of men.

01:36:56.160 --> 01:37:20.540
Then said Jesus unto his disciples, If any man will come after me, let him deny himself, and take up his cross, and follow me. For whosoever will save his life shall lose it, and whosoever will lose his life for my sake shall find it.

01:37:20.540 --> 01:37:32.800
For what is a man profited, if he shall gain the whole world, and lose his own soul? Or what shall a man give in exchange for his soul?

01:37:34.380 --> 01:37:45.280
For the Son of Man shall come in the glory of his Father with his angels, and then he shall reward every man according to his works.

01:37:47.320 --> 01:37:58.960
Verily I say unto you, There be some standing here which shall not taste of death, till they see the Son of Man coming in his kingdom.

01:38:20.067 --> 01:38:28.627
And after six days Jesus taketh Peter, James, and John his brother, and bringeth them up

01:38:28.627 --> 01:38:37.807
into an high mountain apart, and was transfigured before them, and his face did shine as the

01:38:37.807 --> 01:38:45.907
sun, and his raiment was white as the light, and behold there appeared unto them Moses

01:38:45.907 --> 01:38:49.007
and Elias talking with him.

01:38:49.267 --> 01:38:57.127
Then answered Peter, and said unto Jesus, Lord, it is good for us to be here.

01:38:57.287 --> 01:39:04.207
If thou wilt, let us make here three tabernacles, one for thee, and one for Moses, and one

01:39:04.207 --> 01:39:05.807
for Elias.

01:39:06.067 --> 01:39:13.047
While he yet spake, behold, a bright cloud overshadowed them, and behold a voice out

01:39:13.047 --> 01:39:22.567
of the cloud, which said, This is my beloved son, in whom I am well pleased, hear ye him.

01:39:24.107 --> 01:39:30.007
And when the disciples heard it, they fell on their face, and were sore afraid.

01:39:30.727 --> 01:39:38.447
And Jesus came and touched them, and said, Arise, and be not afraid.

01:39:39.407 --> 01:39:44.647
And when they had lifted up their eyes, they saw no man save Jesus only.

01:39:46.807 --> 01:39:54.587
And as they came down from the mountain, Jesus charged them, saying, Tell the vision to no

01:39:54.587 --> 01:39:58.707
man, until the Son of Man be risen again from the dead.

01:39:59.427 --> 01:40:06.947
And his disciples asked him, saying, Why then say the scribes, that Elias must first come?

01:40:07.807 --> 01:40:16.207
And Jesus answered, and said unto them, Elias truly shall first come, and restore all things.

01:40:16.887 --> 01:40:24.087
But I say unto you that Elias is come already, and they knew him not, but have done unto

01:40:24.087 --> 01:40:25.887
him whatsoever they listed.

01:40:26.827 --> 01:40:30.527
Likewise shall also the Son of Man suffer of them.

01:40:31.387 --> 01:40:36.207
Then the disciples understood, that he spake unto them of John the Baptist.

01:40:36.967 --> 01:40:42.487
And when they were come to the multitude, there came to him a certain man, kneeling

01:40:42.487 --> 01:40:51.607
down to him, and saying, Lord, have mercy on my son, for he is lunatic, and sore vexed,

01:40:51.607 --> 01:40:57.127
for often times he falleth into the fire, and oft into the water.

01:40:57.727 --> 01:41:03.007
And I brought him to thy disciples, and they could not cure him.

01:41:03.487 --> 01:41:10.307
Then Jesus answered, and said, O faithless and perverse generation, how long shall I

01:41:10.307 --> 01:41:11.267
be with you?

01:41:11.767 --> 01:41:14.527
How long shall I suffer you?

01:41:15.047 --> 01:41:16.447
Bring him hither to me.

01:41:17.407 --> 01:41:24.927
And Jesus rebuked the devil, and he departed out of him, and the child was cured from that

01:41:24.927 --> 01:41:25.907
very hour.

01:41:26.747 --> 01:41:33.427
Then came the disciples to Jesus apart, and said, Why could not we cast him out?

01:41:34.207 --> 01:41:41.687
And Jesus said unto them, Because of your unbelief, for verily I say unto you, If ye

01:41:41.687 --> 01:41:48.987
have faith as a grain of mustard seed, ye shall say unto this mountain, Remove hence

01:41:48.987 --> 01:41:56.267
to yonder place, and it shall remove, and nothing shall be impossible unto you.

01:41:56.847 --> 01:42:03.007
Howbeit this kind goeth not out, but by prayer and fasting.

01:42:03.527 --> 01:42:10.567
And while they abode in Galilee, Jesus said unto them, The son of man shall be betrayed

01:42:10.567 --> 01:42:17.387
into the hands of men, and they shall kill him, and the third day he shall be raised

01:42:17.387 --> 01:42:18.107
again.

01:42:18.367 --> 01:42:20.227
And they were exceeding sorry.

01:42:21.127 --> 01:42:26.627
And when they were come to Capernaum, they that received tribute money came to Peter,

01:42:27.307 --> 01:42:30.367
and said, Doth not your master pay tribute?

01:42:31.067 --> 01:42:32.627
He sayeth, Yes.

01:42:33.687 --> 01:42:39.827
And when he was come into the house, Jesus prevented him, saying, What thinkest thou,

01:42:39.847 --> 01:42:40.387
Simon?

01:42:41.127 --> 01:42:44.127
Of whom do the kings of the earth take custom or tribute?

01:42:44.727 --> 01:42:46.047
Of their own children?

01:42:46.887 --> 01:42:47.927
Or of strangers?

01:42:48.647 --> 01:42:51.247
Peter sayeth unto him, Of strangers.

01:42:52.307 --> 01:42:56.527
Jesus sayeth unto him, Then are the children free?

01:42:57.367 --> 01:43:04.147
Notwithstanding, lest we should offend them, go thou to the sea, and cast in hook, and

01:43:04.147 --> 01:43:06.707
take up the fish that first cometh up.

01:43:06.987 --> 01:43:13.447
And when thou hast opened his mouth, thou shalt find a piece of money, that take, and

01:43:13.447 --> 01:43:16.547
give unto them, for me and thee.

01:43:38.525 --> 01:43:43.045
At the same time came the disciples unto Jesus, saying,

01:43:43.305 --> 01:43:45.945
Who is the greatest in the kingdom of heaven?

01:43:47.225 --> 01:43:52.125
And Jesus called a little child unto him, And set him in the midst of them,

01:43:52.125 --> 01:43:58.725
And said, Verily I say unto you, Except ye be converted,

01:43:59.105 --> 01:44:04.605
And become as little children, Ye shall not enter into the kingdom of heaven.

01:44:05.425 --> 01:44:09.865
Whosoever therefore shall humble himself as this little child,

01:44:10.525 --> 01:44:13.585
The same is greatest in the kingdom of heaven.

01:44:13.805 --> 01:44:18.705
And whoso shall receive one such little child in my name,

01:44:19.325 --> 01:44:25.105
Receiveth me, but whoso shall offend one of these little ones which believe in me,

01:44:25.645 --> 01:44:29.965
It were better for him that a millstone were hanged about his neck,

01:44:30.505 --> 01:44:33.705
And that he were drowned in the depth of the sea.

01:44:35.085 --> 01:44:43.045
Woe unto the world because of offences, For it must needs be that offences come,

01:44:44.565 --> 01:44:47.705
But woe to that man by whom the offence cometh.

01:44:48.945 --> 01:44:56.025
Wherefore, if thy hand or thy foot offend thee, cut them off, and cast them from thee.

01:44:56.645 --> 01:45:01.445
It is better for thee to enter into life, halt or maimed,

01:45:02.585 --> 01:45:08.165
Rather than having two hands or two feet, to be cast into everlasting fire.

01:45:08.865 --> 01:45:14.185
If thine eye offend thee, pluck it out, and cast it from thee.

01:45:14.185 --> 01:45:19.025
It is better for thee to enter into life with one eye,

01:45:19.145 --> 01:45:24.005
Rather than having two eyes, to be cast into hell fire.

01:45:25.365 --> 01:45:28.845
Take heed that ye despise not one of these little ones,

01:45:29.385 --> 01:45:37.185
For I say unto you that in heaven their angels do always behold the face of my Father which is in heaven,

01:45:37.945 --> 01:45:42.505
For the Son of Man is come to save that which was lost.

01:45:42.505 --> 01:45:50.385
How think ye, if a man have an hundred sheep, and one of them be gone astray,

01:45:50.845 --> 01:45:55.425
Doth he not leave the ninety and nine, and goeth into the mountains,

01:45:55.985 --> 01:45:58.465
And seeketh that which is gone astray?

01:45:59.065 --> 01:46:03.165
And if so be that he find it, verily I say unto you,

01:46:03.565 --> 01:46:10.165
He rejoiceth more for that sheep, than of the ninety and nine which went not astray.

01:46:10.165 --> 01:46:14.905
Even so, it is not the will of your Father which is in heaven,

01:46:15.325 --> 01:46:17.945
That one of these little ones should perish.

01:46:18.425 --> 01:46:22.585
Moreover, if thy brother shall trespass against thee,

01:46:22.885 --> 01:46:27.205
Go and tell him his fault, between thee and him alone.

01:46:27.865 --> 01:46:31.725
If he shall hear thee, thou hast gained thy brother.

01:46:32.805 --> 01:46:37.585
But if he will not hear thee, then take with thee one or two more,

01:46:37.585 --> 01:46:42.565
That in the mouth of two or three witnesses every word may be established.

01:46:43.525 --> 01:46:48.285
And if he shall neglect to hear them, tell it unto the church.

01:46:49.125 --> 01:46:57.505
But if he neglect to hear the church, let him be unto thee as an heathen man and a publican.

01:46:58.025 --> 01:47:04.025
Verily I say unto you, whatsoever ye shall bind on earth shall be bound in heaven,

01:47:04.025 --> 01:47:09.725
And whatsoever ye shall loose on earth shall be loosed in heaven.

01:47:10.645 --> 01:47:17.805
Again I say unto you, that if two of you shall agree on earth as touching anything that they shall ask,

01:47:17.925 --> 01:47:21.385
It shall be done for them of my Father which is in heaven.

01:47:22.005 --> 01:47:28.845
For where two or three are gathered together in my name, there am I in the midst of them.

01:47:29.445 --> 01:47:38.025
Then came Peter to him, and said, Lord, how oft shall my brother sin against me, and I forgive him, till seven times?

01:47:38.905 --> 01:47:47.405
Jesus saith unto him, I say not unto thee, until seven times, but until seventy times seven.

01:47:48.685 --> 01:47:55.225
Therefore is the kingdom of heaven likened unto a certain king, which would take account of his servants.

01:47:55.685 --> 01:48:03.365
And when he had begun to reckon, one was brought unto him which owed him ten thousand talents.

01:48:04.165 --> 01:48:16.425
But for as much as he had not to pay, his Lord commanded him to be sold, and his wife and children, and all that he had, and payment to be made.

01:48:16.425 --> 01:48:25.625
The servant therefore fell down, and worshipped him, saying, Lord, have patience with me, and I will pay thee all.

01:48:26.865 --> 01:48:33.865
Then the Lord of that servant was moved with compassion, and loosed him, and forgave him the debt.

01:48:34.505 --> 01:48:42.245
But the same servant went out, and found one of his fellow-servants, which owed him an hundred pence.

01:48:42.245 --> 01:48:49.885
And he laid hands on him, and took him by the throat, saying, Pay me that thou owest.

01:48:50.885 --> 01:48:58.685
And his fellow-servant fell down at his feet, and besought him, saying, Have patience with me, and I will pay thee all.

01:48:59.165 --> 01:49:05.925
And he would not, but went and cast him into prison, till he should pay the debt.

01:49:06.745 --> 01:49:16.345
So when his fellow-servants saw what was done, they were very sorry, and came and told unto their Lord all that was done.

01:49:16.685 --> 01:49:27.925
Then his Lord, after that he had called him, said unto him, O thou wicked servant, I forgave thee all that debt because thou desirest me.

01:49:28.705 --> 01:49:35.305
Shouldest not thou also have had compassion on thy fellow-servant, even as I had pity on thee?

01:49:35.305 --> 01:49:44.565
And his Lord was wrath, and delivered him to the tormentors, till he should pay all that was due unto him.

01:49:45.045 --> 01:49:55.185
So likewise shall my Heavenly Father do also unto you, if ye from your hearts forgive not every one his brother their trespasses.

01:50:15.728 --> 01:50:21.548
And it came to pass, that when Jesus had finished these sayings,

01:50:21.948 --> 01:50:26.888
he departed from Galilee and came into the coasts of Judea beyond Jordan,

01:50:27.268 --> 01:50:31.688
and great multitudes followed him, and he healed them there.

01:50:31.688 --> 01:50:37.268
The Pharisees also came unto him, tempting him, and saying unto him,

01:50:37.748 --> 01:50:42.888
Is it lawful for a man to put away his wife for every cause?

01:50:44.008 --> 01:50:48.008
And he answered and said unto them, Have ye not read,

01:50:48.388 --> 01:50:53.088
that he which made them at the beginning made them male and female,

01:50:53.488 --> 01:50:58.648
and said, For this cause shall a man leave his father and mother,

01:50:58.648 --> 01:51:05.728
and shall cleave to his wife, and they twain shall be one flesh?

01:51:07.368 --> 01:51:11.028
Wherefore, they are no more twain but one flesh.

01:51:12.088 --> 01:51:16.768
What therefore God hath joined together, let not man put asunder.

01:51:17.768 --> 01:51:23.648
They say unto him, Why did Moses then command to give a writing of

01:51:23.648 --> 01:51:31.628
and to put her away? He saith unto them, Moses, because of the hardness of your hearts,

01:51:32.248 --> 01:51:37.568
suffered you to put away your wives. But from the beginning it was not so.

01:51:38.868 --> 01:51:42.568
And I say unto you, Whosoever shall put away his wife,

01:51:43.368 --> 01:51:48.268
except it be for fornication, and shall marry another committeth adultery,

01:51:48.768 --> 01:51:53.268
and whoso marryeth her which is put away, doth commit adultery.

01:51:55.088 --> 01:51:59.988
His disciples say unto him, If the case of the man be so with his wife,

01:52:00.308 --> 01:52:03.388
it is not good to marry. But he said unto them,

01:52:03.648 --> 01:52:09.008
All men cannot receive this saying, save they to whom it is given.

01:52:09.508 --> 01:52:13.908
For there are some eunuchs which were so born from their mother's womb,

01:52:14.828 --> 01:52:19.668
and there are some eunuchs which were made eunuchs of men,

01:52:19.668 --> 01:52:26.488
and there be eunuchs which have made themselves eunuchs for the kingdom of heaven's sake.

01:52:27.708 --> 01:52:31.328
He that is able to receive it, let him receive it.

01:52:33.088 --> 01:52:39.308
Then were there brought unto him little children, that he should put his hands on them and pray.

01:52:39.828 --> 01:52:43.528
And the disciples rebuked them. But Jesus said,

01:52:43.528 --> 01:52:47.828
Suffer little children, and forbid them not to come unto me.

01:52:48.268 --> 01:52:54.688
For such is the kingdom of heaven. And he laid his hands on them, and departed thence.

01:52:55.208 --> 01:53:02.788
And behold, one came and said unto him, Good master, what good things shall I do,

01:53:03.068 --> 01:53:06.788
that I may have eternal life? And he said unto him,

01:53:07.408 --> 01:53:12.388
Why callest thou me good? There is none good, but one that is God.

01:53:12.388 --> 01:53:16.748
But if thou wilt enter into life, keep the commandments.

01:53:17.648 --> 01:53:23.028
He saith unto him, Which? Jesus said, Thou shalt do no murder,

01:53:23.548 --> 01:53:26.728
Thou shalt not commit adultery, Thou shalt not steal,

01:53:27.308 --> 01:53:32.088
Thou shalt not bear false witness, Honor thy father and thy mother,

01:53:32.608 --> 01:53:35.368
And thou shalt love thy neighbor as thyself.

01:53:36.608 --> 01:53:41.588
The young man saith unto him, All these things have I kept from my youth up,

01:53:41.588 --> 01:53:47.548
What lack I yet? Jesus said unto him, If thou wilt be perfect,

01:53:48.068 --> 01:53:52.008
Go, and sell that thou hast, And give to the poor,

01:53:52.608 --> 01:53:57.208
And thou shalt have treasure in heaven, And come and follow me.

01:53:57.668 --> 01:54:01.568
But when the young man heard that saying, He went away sorrowful,

01:54:01.748 --> 01:54:07.148
For he had great possessions. Then said Jesus unto his disciples,

01:54:08.128 --> 01:54:15.048
Verily I say unto you, That a rich man shall hardly enter into the kingdom of heaven.

01:54:16.168 --> 01:54:22.868
And again I say unto you, It is easier for a camel to go through the eye of a needle,

01:54:24.188 --> 01:54:27.268
Than for a rich man to enter into the kingdom of God.

01:54:27.928 --> 01:54:33.448
When his disciples heard it, they were exceedingly amazed, saying, Who then can be saved?

01:54:34.388 --> 01:54:40.448
But Jesus beheld them and said unto them, With men this is impossible,

01:54:41.288 --> 01:54:47.208
But with God all things are possible. Then answered Peter and said unto him,

01:54:47.408 --> 01:54:53.168
Behold, we have forsaken all and followed thee, What shall we have therefore?

01:54:53.808 --> 01:54:58.368
And Jesus said unto them, Verily I say unto you,

01:54:58.868 --> 01:55:05.568
That ye which have followed me in the regeneration, When the Son of Man shall sit in the throne of his

01:55:05.568 --> 01:55:13.648
glory, Ye also shall sit upon twelve thrones, Judging the twelve tribes of Israel.

01:55:14.208 --> 01:55:21.888
And every one that hath forsaken houses, Or brethren, or sisters, or father, or mother,

01:55:21.888 --> 01:55:29.808
Or wife, or children, or lands, for my name's sake, Shall receive an hundred fold,

01:55:30.428 --> 01:55:37.688
And shall inherit everlasting life. But many that are first shall be last,

01:55:38.088 --> 01:55:41.028
And the last shall be first.

01:56:02.301 --> 01:56:09.861
For the kingdom of heaven is like unto a man that is an householder, which went out early

01:56:09.861 --> 01:56:12.961
in the morning to hire labourers into his vineyard.

01:56:13.221 --> 01:56:19.661
And when he had agreed with the labourers for a penny a day, he sent them into his vineyard,

01:56:19.661 --> 01:56:25.201
and he went out about the third hour and saw others standing idle in the market place,

01:56:25.861 --> 01:56:31.901
and said unto them, Go ye also into the vineyard, and whatsoever is right I will give you.

01:56:32.041 --> 01:56:39.001
And they went their way. Again he went out about the sixth and ninth hour, and did likewise.

01:56:39.601 --> 01:56:43.241
And about the eleventh hour he went out and found others standing idle,

01:56:43.901 --> 01:56:48.101
and saith unto them, Why stand ye here all the day idle?

01:56:49.061 --> 01:56:53.041
And they say unto him, Because no man hath hired us,

01:56:54.261 --> 01:56:58.441
he saith unto them, Go ye also into the vineyard,

01:56:58.841 --> 01:57:06.681
and whatsoever is right that shall ye receive. So when even was come, the lord of the vineyard

01:57:06.681 --> 01:57:12.641
saith unto his steward, Call the labourers, and give them their hire,

01:57:12.641 --> 01:57:19.241
beginning from the last unto the first. And when they came that were hired about

01:57:19.241 --> 01:57:26.661
the eleventh hour, they received every man a penny. But when the first came, they supposed

01:57:26.661 --> 01:57:32.121
that they should have received more, and they likewise received every man a penny.

01:57:33.181 --> 01:57:38.661
And when they had received it, they murmured against the good man of the house, saying,

01:57:38.661 --> 01:57:45.141
These last have wrought but one hour, and thou hast made them equal unto us,

01:57:45.401 --> 01:57:49.241
which have borne the burden and the heat of the day.

01:57:49.781 --> 01:57:53.801
But he answered one of them, and said, Friend, I do thee no wrong.

01:57:54.401 --> 01:57:59.801
Dost not thou agree with me for a penny? Take that thine is, and go thy way.

01:58:00.081 --> 01:58:06.881
I will give unto this last even as unto thee. Is it not lawful for me to do what I will with mine

01:58:07.621 --> 01:58:15.801
Is thine eye evil because I am good? So the last shall be first, and the first

01:58:15.801 --> 01:58:25.801
last, for many be called, but few chosen. And Jesus, going up to Jerusalem, took the

01:58:25.801 --> 01:58:33.441
twelve disciples apart in the way, and said unto them, Behold, we go up to Jerusalem,

01:58:34.281 --> 01:58:40.561
and the son of man shall be betrayed unto the chief priests, and unto the scribes,

01:58:41.181 --> 01:58:48.581
and they shall condemn him to death, and shall deliver him to the Gentiles to mock,

01:58:49.401 --> 01:58:57.401
and to scourge, and to crucify him. And the third day he shall rise again.

01:58:57.881 --> 01:59:03.421
Then came to him the mother of Zebedee's children, with her sons worshiping him,

01:59:03.441 --> 01:59:11.121
and desiring a certain thing of him. And he said unto her, What wilt thou? She sayeth unto him,

01:59:12.681 --> 01:59:21.401
Grant that these my two sons may sit, the one on thy right hand, and the other on thy left in thy

01:59:21.401 --> 01:59:30.121
kingdom. But Jesus answered and said, Ye know not what ye ask. Are ye able to drink of the cup that

01:59:30.121 --> 01:59:38.821
I shall drink of, and be baptized with the baptism that I am baptized with? They say unto him,

01:59:39.101 --> 01:59:48.901
We are able, and he sayeth unto them, Ye shall drink indeed of my cup, and be baptized with the

01:59:48.901 --> 01:59:57.261
baptism that I am baptized with. But to sit on my right hand and on my left is not mine to give,

01:59:57.261 --> 02:00:02.401
but it shall be given to them for whom it is prepared of my father.

02:00:03.621 --> 02:00:09.601
And when the ten heard it, they were moved with indignation against the two brethren.

02:00:10.901 --> 02:00:18.441
But Jesus called them unto him and said, Ye know that the princes of the Gentiles exercise

02:00:18.441 --> 02:00:24.921
dominion over them, and they that are great exercise authority upon them.

02:00:25.881 --> 02:00:32.361
But it shall not be so among you, but whosoever will be great among you,

02:00:33.101 --> 02:00:40.901
let him be your minister. And whosoever shall be chief among you, let him be your servant,

02:00:41.561 --> 02:00:50.401
even as the Son of Man came not to be ministered unto, but to minister, and to give his life a

02:00:50.401 --> 02:00:57.981
ransom for many. And as they departed from Jericho, a great multitude followed him.

02:00:58.461 --> 02:01:04.301
And behold, two blind men sitting by the wayside, when they heard that Jesus passed by,

02:01:04.461 --> 02:01:11.861
cried out, saying, Have mercy on us, O Lord, thou Son of David. And the multitude rebuked them,

02:01:12.001 --> 02:01:18.701
because they should hold their peace. But they cried the more, saying, Have mercy on us,

02:01:18.701 --> 02:01:27.841
O Lord, thou Son of David. And Jesus stood still, and called them, and said, What will ye that I

02:01:27.841 --> 02:01:36.401
shall do unto you? They say unto him, Lord, that our eyes may be opened. So Jesus had compassion on

02:01:36.401 --> 02:01:44.421
them, and touched their eyes, and immediately their eyes received sight, and they followed him.

02:01:54.399 --> 02:01:55.079
21.

02:02:04.839 --> 02:02:11.639
And when they drew nigh unto Jerusalem, and were come to Bethphagi unto the Mount of Olives,

02:02:12.319 --> 02:02:18.559
then sent Jesus two disciples, saying unto them, Go into the village over against you,

02:02:18.559 --> 02:02:26.579
and straightway ye shall find an ass tied, and a colt with her, loose them, and bring them unto me.

02:02:26.959 --> 02:02:32.979
And if any man say aught unto you, ye shall say, The Lord hath need of them,

02:02:33.199 --> 02:02:35.179
and straightway he will send them.

02:02:35.979 --> 02:02:41.299
All this was done that it might be fulfilled which was spoken by the prophet, saying,

02:02:42.019 --> 02:02:48.179
Tell ye the daughter of Sion, behold thy king cometh unto thee, meek.

02:02:48.559 --> 02:02:53.839
And sitting upon an ass, and a colt, the foal of an ass.

02:02:54.779 --> 02:03:00.799
And the disciples went, and did as Jesus commanded them, and brought the ass, and the colt,

02:03:01.179 --> 02:03:05.419
and put on them their clothes, and they set him thereon.

02:03:06.299 --> 02:03:13.179
And a very great multitude spread their garments in the way, others cut down branches from the trees,

02:03:13.179 --> 02:03:15.759
and strawed them in the way.

02:03:17.139 --> 02:03:21.459
And the multitudes that went before, and that followed, cried, saying,

02:03:21.839 --> 02:03:27.679
Hosanna to the son of David, blessed is he that cometh in the name of the Lord,

02:03:28.259 --> 02:03:29.899
Hosanna in the highest.

02:03:30.959 --> 02:03:38.219
And when he was come into Jerusalem, all the city was moved, saying, Who is this?

02:03:38.799 --> 02:03:45.499
And the multitude said, This is Jesus, the prophet of Nazareth, of Galilee.

02:03:46.599 --> 02:03:55.019
And Jesus went into the temple of God, and cast out all them that sold and bought in the temple,

02:03:55.519 --> 02:04:01.999
and overthrew the tables of the money changers, and the seats of them that sold doves.

02:04:02.959 --> 02:04:10.099
And said unto them, It is written, My house shall be called a house of prayer,

02:04:11.339 --> 02:04:13.539
but ye have made it a den of thieves.

02:04:15.059 --> 02:04:20.639
And the blind and the lame came to him in the temple, and he healed them.

02:04:21.459 --> 02:04:27.019
And when the chief priests and scribes saw the wonderful things that he did,

02:04:27.019 --> 02:04:33.199
and the children crying in the temple, and saying, Hosanna to the son of David,

02:04:33.819 --> 02:04:35.579
they were sore displeased.

02:04:36.639 --> 02:04:40.639
And said unto him, Hearest thou what these say?

02:04:41.599 --> 02:04:48.379
And Jesus saith unto them, Yea, have ye never read, out of the mouth of babes and sucklings,

02:04:48.939 --> 02:04:50.859
thou hast perfected praise.

02:04:51.519 --> 02:04:58.219
And he left them, and went out of the city into Bethany, and he lodged there.

02:04:59.139 --> 02:05:03.239
Now in the morning, as he returned into the city, he hungered.

02:05:03.959 --> 02:05:11.039
And when he saw a fig tree in the way, he came to it, and found nothing thereon but leaves only.

02:05:11.719 --> 02:05:16.959
And said unto it, Let no fruit grow on thee henceforth forever.

02:05:17.759 --> 02:05:20.579
And presently the fig tree withered away.

02:05:22.099 --> 02:05:27.879
And when the disciples saw it, they marveled, saying, How soon is the fig tree withered away?

02:05:29.379 --> 02:05:33.979
Jesus answered and said unto them, Verily I say unto you,

02:05:34.439 --> 02:05:42.119
If ye have faith, and doubt not, ye shall not only do this which is done to the fig tree,

02:05:42.119 --> 02:05:50.719
but also if ye shall say unto this mountain, Be thou removed, and be thou cast into the sea,

02:05:50.919 --> 02:05:52.139
it shall be done.

02:05:52.819 --> 02:05:59.159
And all things whatsoever ye shall ask in prayer believing, ye shall receive.

02:06:00.799 --> 02:06:04.639
And when he was come into the temple, the chief priests

02:06:04.639 --> 02:06:09.919
and the elders of the people came unto him as he was teaching, and said,

02:06:09.919 --> 02:06:16.659
By what authority doest thou these things? And who gave thee this authority?

02:06:17.979 --> 02:06:23.179
And Jesus answered and said unto them, I will also ask you one thing,

02:06:23.879 --> 02:06:29.419
which if ye tell me, I in like wise will tell you by what authority I do these things.

02:06:30.399 --> 02:06:36.459
The baptism of John, once was it, from heaven or of men?

02:06:37.399 --> 02:06:43.379
And they reasoned with themselves, saying, If we say from heaven, he will say unto us,

02:06:43.519 --> 02:06:50.479
why did ye not then believe him? But if we shall say of men, we fear the people,

02:06:50.899 --> 02:06:53.059
for all hold John as a prophet.

02:06:53.979 --> 02:06:59.059
And they answered Jesus and said, We cannot tell.

02:06:59.999 --> 02:07:05.999
And he said unto them, Neither tell I you by what authority I do these things.

02:07:06.459 --> 02:07:10.899
But what think ye? A certain man had two sons,

02:07:11.499 --> 02:07:16.319
and he came to the first and said, Son, go work today in my vineyard.

02:07:16.899 --> 02:07:22.079
He answered and said, I will not, but afterward he repented and went.

02:07:22.899 --> 02:07:30.419
And he came to the second and said likewise, and he answered and said, I go, sir, and went not.

02:07:31.219 --> 02:07:37.339
Whether of them twain did the will of his father? They say unto him, the first.

02:07:38.399 --> 02:07:42.279
Jesus sayeth unto them, Verily I say unto you,

02:07:42.599 --> 02:07:47.929
that the publicans and the harlots go into the kingdom of God before you.

02:07:48.919 --> 02:07:54.279
For John came unto you in the way of righteousness, and ye believed him not.

02:07:54.819 --> 02:08:01.219
But the publicans and the harlots believed him, and ye, when ye had seen it,

02:08:02.099 --> 02:08:05.559
repented not afterward that ye might believe him.

02:08:06.159 --> 02:08:11.559
Here another parable. There was a certain householder which planted a vineyard,

02:08:11.959 --> 02:08:17.379
and hedged it round about, and digged a winepress in it, and built a tower,

02:08:17.799 --> 02:08:21.979
and let it out to husbandmen, and went into a far country.

02:08:22.979 --> 02:08:28.459
And when the time of the fruit drew near, he sent his servants to the husbandmen,

02:08:28.759 --> 02:08:34.319
that they might receive the fruits of it. And the husbandmen took his servants,

02:08:34.959 --> 02:08:42.199
and beat one, and killed another, and stoned another. Again, he sent other servants more

02:08:42.199 --> 02:08:50.559
than the first, and they did unto them likewise. But last of all, he sent unto them his sons,

02:08:50.559 --> 02:08:56.859
saying, They will reverence my son. But when the husbandmen saw the son,

02:08:57.399 --> 02:09:02.359
they said among themselves, This is the heir, come, let us kill him,

02:09:02.679 --> 02:09:10.419
and let us seize on his inheritance. And they caught him, and cast him out of the vineyard,

02:09:10.739 --> 02:09:15.359
and slew him. When the Lord therefore of the vineyard cometh,

02:09:15.979 --> 02:09:23.539
What will he do unto those husbandmen? They say unto him, He will miserably destroy

02:09:23.539 --> 02:09:29.199
those wicked men, and will let out his vineyard unto other husbandmen,

02:09:29.479 --> 02:09:35.699
which shall render him the fruits in their seasons. Jesus saith unto them, Did ye never

02:09:35.699 --> 02:09:42.659
read in the scriptures? The stone which the builders rejected, the same is become the head

02:09:42.659 --> 02:09:51.619
of the corner. This is the Lord's doing, and it is marvelous in our eyes. Therefore say I unto you,

02:09:51.839 --> 02:09:58.619
The kingdom of God shall be taken from you, and given to a nation bringing forth the fruits

02:09:58.619 --> 02:10:07.739
thereof. And whosoever shall fall on this stone shall be broken, but on whomsoever it shall fall.

02:10:08.579 --> 02:10:16.079
It will grind him to powder. And when the chief priests and Pharisees had heard his parables,

02:10:17.059 --> 02:10:22.159
they perceived that he spake of them. But when they sought to lay hands on him,

02:10:22.239 --> 02:10:26.099
they feared the multitude, because they took him for a prophet.

02:10:45.051 --> 02:10:50.671
22 And Jesus answered, and spake unto them again

02:10:50.671 --> 02:10:56.551
by parables, and said, The kingdom of heaven is like unto a certain

02:10:56.551 --> 02:11:02.691
king which made a marriage for his son, and sent forth his servants to call them that

02:11:02.691 --> 02:11:05.871
were bidden to the wedding, and they would not come.

02:11:06.311 --> 02:11:12.771
Again he sent forth other servants, saying, Tell them which are bidden, behold, I have

02:11:12.771 --> 02:11:19.091
prepared my dinner, my oxen and my fatlings are killed, and all things are ready.

02:11:19.611 --> 02:11:20.971
Come unto the marriage.

02:11:21.611 --> 02:11:28.371
But they made light of it, and went their ways, one to his farm, another to his merchandise.

02:11:28.371 --> 02:11:33.791
And the remnant took his servants, and entreated them spitefully, and slew them.

02:11:34.931 --> 02:11:40.531
But when the king heard thereof he was wroth, and he sent forth his armies,

02:11:41.031 --> 02:11:45.171
and destroyed those murderers, and burned up their city.

02:11:46.131 --> 02:11:51.731
Then saith he to his servants, The wedding is ready, but they which were

02:11:51.731 --> 02:11:53.431
bidden were not worthy.

02:11:53.911 --> 02:12:01.131
Go ye therefore into the highways, and as many as ye shall find, bid to the marriage.

02:12:02.011 --> 02:12:08.251
So those servants went out into the highways, and gathered together all as many as they

02:12:08.251 --> 02:12:10.811
found, both bad and good.

02:12:11.591 --> 02:12:14.071
And the wedding was furnished with guests.

02:12:15.031 --> 02:12:22.011
And when the king came in to see the guests, he saw there a man which had not on a wedding

02:12:22.011 --> 02:12:22.671
garment.

02:12:23.291 --> 02:12:29.711
And he saith unto him, Friend, how camest thou in hither not having a wedding garment?

02:12:30.151 --> 02:12:31.511
And he was speechless.

02:12:32.431 --> 02:12:38.971
Then said the king to the servants, Bind him hand and foot, and take him away,

02:12:39.291 --> 02:12:42.291
and cast him into outer darkness.

02:12:43.131 --> 02:12:46.291
There shall be weeping, and gnashing of teeth.

02:12:47.131 --> 02:12:50.431
For many are called, but few are chosen.

02:12:51.261 --> 02:12:57.411
Then went the Pharisees, and took counsel how they might entangle him in his talk.

02:12:58.631 --> 02:13:02.831
And they sent out unto him their disciples with the Herodians, saying,

02:13:03.351 --> 02:13:09.551
Master, we know that thou art true, and teachest the way of God in truth.

02:13:10.151 --> 02:13:15.751
Neither carest thou for any man, for thou regardest not the person of men.

02:13:16.551 --> 02:13:18.691
Tell us therefore what thinkest thou?

02:13:19.371 --> 02:13:24.031
Is it lawful to give tribute unto Caesar, or not?

02:13:24.771 --> 02:13:30.231
But Jesus perceived their wickedness, and said, Why tempt ye me, ye hypocrites?

02:13:31.231 --> 02:13:34.751
Show me the tribute money, and they brought unto him a penny.

02:13:35.471 --> 02:13:40.931
And he saith unto them, Whose is this image and superscription?

02:13:41.991 --> 02:13:44.431
They say unto him, Caesar's.

02:13:44.591 --> 02:13:46.331
Then saith he unto them.

02:13:46.331 --> 02:13:52.311
Render therefore unto Caesar the things which are Caesar's,

02:13:52.331 --> 02:13:55.531
and unto God the things that are God's.

02:13:55.731 --> 02:14:00.811
When they had heard these words, they marveled, and left him, and went their way.

02:14:01.231 --> 02:14:07.151
The same day came to him the Sadducees, which saith that there is no resurrection,

02:14:07.691 --> 02:14:14.731
and asked him, saying, Master, Moses said, If a man die having no children,

02:14:14.731 --> 02:14:20.371
his brother shall marry his wife, and raise up seed unto his brother.

02:14:21.231 --> 02:14:27.671
Now there were with a seven brethren, and the first, when he had married a wife, deceased,

02:14:28.131 --> 02:14:31.791
and having no issue, left his wife unto his brother.

02:14:32.551 --> 02:14:36.811
Likewise the second also, and the third unto the seventh.

02:14:37.731 --> 02:14:42.271
And last of all the woman died also. Therefore in the resurrection,

02:14:42.831 --> 02:14:47.851
whose wife shall she be of the seven? For they all had her.

02:14:48.211 --> 02:14:54.531
Jesus answered and said unto them, Ye do err, not knowing the scriptures nor the power of God.

02:14:55.251 --> 02:14:59.831
For in the resurrection they neither marry nor are given in marriage,

02:15:00.591 --> 02:15:06.311
but are as the angels of God in heaven, but as touching the resurrection of the dead.

02:15:06.891 --> 02:15:13.951
Have ye not read that which was spoken unto you by God, saying, I am the God of Abraham,

02:15:14.431 --> 02:15:21.771
and the God of Isaac, and the God of Jacob? God is not the God of the dead, but of the living.

02:15:22.771 --> 02:15:27.831
And when the multitude heard this, they were astonished at his doctrine.

02:15:28.251 --> 02:15:32.831
But when the Pharisees had heard that he had put the Sadducees to silence,

02:15:33.411 --> 02:15:38.531
they were gathered together. Then one of them, which was a lawyer, asked him a question,

02:15:38.751 --> 02:15:45.411
tempting him, and saying, Master, which is the greatest commandment in the law?

02:15:46.331 --> 02:15:51.751
Jesus said unto him, Thou shalt love the Lord thy God with all thy heart,

02:15:52.191 --> 02:15:58.171
and with all thy soul, and with all thy mind. This is the first and great commandment.

02:15:59.031 --> 02:16:04.231
And the second is like unto it. Thou shalt love thy neighbor as thyself.

02:16:05.231 --> 02:16:10.171
On these two commandments hang all the law and the prophets.

02:16:10.831 --> 02:16:17.331
While the Pharisees were gathered together, Jesus asked them, saying, What think ye of Christ?

02:16:18.451 --> 02:16:25.931
Whose son is he? They say unto him, The son of David. He sayeth unto them, How then doth David

02:16:25.931 --> 02:16:32.111
in spirit call him Lord, saying, The Lord said unto my Lord,

02:16:32.891 --> 02:16:37.591
Set thou on my right hand till I make thine enemies thy footstool.

02:16:38.991 --> 02:16:48.271
If David then called him Lord, how is he his son? And no man was able to answer him a word.

02:16:48.931 --> 02:16:53.731
Neither durst any man from that day forth ask him any more questions.

02:17:15.429 --> 02:17:20.529
Then spake Jesus to the multitude and to his disciples, saying,

02:17:21.229 --> 02:17:25.369
The scribes and the Pharisees sit in Moses' seat.

02:17:26.549 --> 02:17:30.649
All therefore whatsoever they bid you observe, that observe and do.

02:17:30.649 --> 02:17:38.669
But do not ye after their works, for they say and do not, for they bind heavy burdens,

02:17:39.289 --> 02:17:43.869
and grievous to be born, and lay them on men's shoulders.

02:17:44.849 --> 02:17:48.749
But they themselves will not move them with one of their fingers.

02:17:50.409 --> 02:17:57.169
But all their works they do for to be seen of men, they make broad their phylacteries,

02:17:57.169 --> 02:18:04.669
and enlarge the borders of their garments, and love the uppermost rooms at feasts,

02:18:04.989 --> 02:18:09.569
and the chief seats in the synagogues, and greetings in the markets,

02:18:09.729 --> 02:18:15.889
and to be called of men Rabbi, Rabbi. But be not ye called Rabbi,

02:18:17.089 --> 02:18:21.289
for one is your Master, even Christ, and ye are all brethren.

02:18:22.149 --> 02:18:29.609
And call no man your Father upon the earth, for one is your Father, which is in heaven,

02:18:30.649 --> 02:18:37.429
neither be ye called Masters, for one is your Master, even Christ.

02:18:38.149 --> 02:18:47.149
But he that is greatest among you shall be your servant, and whosoever shall exalt himself shall

02:18:47.149 --> 02:18:53.889
be abased, and he that shall humble himself shall be exalted.

02:18:55.549 --> 02:19:04.349
But woe unto you, scribes and Pharisees, hypocrites, for ye shut up the kingdom of heaven against men,

02:19:04.589 --> 02:19:10.569
for ye neither go in yourselves, neither suffer ye them that are entering to go in.

02:19:11.529 --> 02:19:19.529
Woe unto you, scribes and Pharisees, hypocrites, for ye devour widows' houses,

02:19:20.149 --> 02:19:27.809
and for a pretense make long prayer, therefore ye shall receive the greater damnation.

02:19:28.529 --> 02:19:39.069
Woe unto you, scribes and Pharisees, hypocrites, for ye compass sea and land to make one proselyte,

02:19:39.069 --> 02:19:45.369
and when he is made ye make him twofold more the child of hell than yourselves.

02:19:45.949 --> 02:19:54.269
Woe unto you, blind guides, which say whosoever shall swear by the temple, it is nothing,

02:19:54.709 --> 02:20:01.749
but whosoever shall swear by the gold of the temple, he is a debtor, ye fools and blind,

02:20:02.149 --> 02:20:07.909
for whither is greater, the gold or the temple that sanctifyeth the gold?

02:20:08.789 --> 02:20:12.949
And whosoever shall swear by the altar, it is nothing,

02:20:13.449 --> 02:20:20.549
but whosoever sweareth by the gift that is upon it, he is guilty, ye fools and blind,

02:20:20.729 --> 02:20:26.129
for whither is greater, the gift or the altar that sanctifyeth the gift?

02:20:27.009 --> 02:20:33.389
Whoso therefore shall swear by the altar, sweareth by it and by all things thereon,

02:20:33.389 --> 02:20:40.749
and whoso shall swear by the temple, sweareth by it and by him that dwelleth therein,

02:20:41.189 --> 02:20:48.249
and he that shall swear by heaven, sweareth by the throne of God and by him that sitteth thereon.

02:20:49.489 --> 02:20:58.369
Woe unto you, scribes and Pharisees, hypocrites, for ye pay a tithe of mint and anise and cummin,

02:20:58.369 --> 02:21:04.849
and have omitted the weightier matters of the law, judgment, mercy, and faith,

02:21:05.449 --> 02:21:12.649
these ought ye to have done, and not to leave the other undone, ye blind guides,

02:21:13.189 --> 02:21:23.609
which strain out a gnat, and swallow a camel, woe unto you, scribes and Pharisees, hypocrites,

02:21:24.329 --> 02:21:33.669
for ye make clean the outside of the cup and of the platter, but within they are full of extortion

02:21:33.669 --> 02:21:42.169
and excess, thou blind Pharisee, cleanse first that which is within the cup and platter,

02:21:43.089 --> 02:21:51.169
that the outside of them may be clean also, woe unto you, scribes and Pharisees, hypocrites,

02:21:51.669 --> 02:22:00.449
for ye are like unto whited sepulchres, which indeed appear beautiful outward, but are within

02:22:00.449 --> 02:22:10.329
full of dead men's bones and of all uncleanness, even so ye also outwardly appear righteous unto

02:22:10.329 --> 02:22:22.309
men, but within are full of hypocrisy and iniquity, woe unto you, scribes and Pharisees,

02:22:22.449 --> 02:22:30.789
hypocrites, because ye build the tombs of the prophets, and garnish the sepulchres of the

02:22:30.789 --> 02:22:38.529
righteous, and say, if we had been in the days of our fathers, we would not have been partakers

02:22:38.529 --> 02:22:45.269
with them in the blood of the prophets, wherefore ye be witnesses unto yourselves that ye are the

02:22:45.269 --> 02:22:55.729
children of them which killed the prophets, fill ye up with the measure of your fathers, ye serpents,

02:22:56.009 --> 02:23:06.089
ye generation of vipers, how can ye escape the damnation of hell, wherefore behold, I send unto

02:23:06.089 --> 02:23:16.509
you prophets and wise men and scribes, some of them ye shall kill and crucify, and some of them

02:23:16.509 --> 02:23:24.689
shall ye scourge in your synagogues and persecute them from city to city, that upon you may come all

02:23:24.689 --> 02:23:32.329
the righteous blood shed upon the earth, from the blood of righteous Abel, unto the blood of

02:23:32.329 --> 02:23:41.409
Zechariah, son of Barakaius, whom ye slew between the temple and the altar, verily I say unto you,

02:23:42.029 --> 02:23:45.329
all these things shall come upon this generation.

02:23:46.929 --> 02:23:56.169
O Jerusalem, Jerusalem, thou that killest the prophets and stonest them which are sent unto

02:23:56.169 --> 02:24:04.509
thee, how often would I have gathered thy children together, even as a hen gathereth her chickens

02:24:04.509 --> 02:24:13.369
under her wings, but ye would not, behold, your house is left unto you desolate,

02:24:14.909 --> 02:24:22.169
for I say unto you, ye shall not see me henceforth, till ye shall say,

02:24:22.169 --> 02:24:26.449
Blessed is he that cometh in the name of the Lord.

02:24:36.875 --> 02:24:37.515
24.

02:24:47.735 --> 02:24:53.875
And Jesus went out, and departed from the temple, and his disciples came to him for

02:24:53.875 --> 02:24:56.255
to show him the buildings of the temple.

02:24:57.035 --> 02:25:04.795
And Jesus said unto them, See ye not all these things, verily I say unto you, there shall

02:25:04.795 --> 02:25:11.155
not be left here one stone upon another that shall not be thrown down.

02:25:11.775 --> 02:25:18.055
And as he sat upon the Mount of Olives, the disciples came unto him privately, saying,

02:25:18.455 --> 02:25:26.175
Tell us, when shall these things be, and what shall be the sign of thy coming, and of the

02:25:26.175 --> 02:25:27.215
end of the world?

02:25:28.175 --> 02:25:35.835
And Jesus answered and said unto them, Take heed that no man deceive you, for many shall

02:25:35.835 --> 02:25:41.695
come in my name, saying, I am the Christ, and shall deceive many.

02:25:42.455 --> 02:25:51.295
And ye shall hear of wars and rumors of wars, see that ye be not troubled, for all these

02:25:51.295 --> 02:25:53.235
things must come to pass.

02:25:54.015 --> 02:26:02.375
But the end is not yet, for nation shall rise against nation, and kingdom against kingdom,

02:26:03.235 --> 02:26:08.275
and there shall be famines and pestilences and earthquakes in diverse places.

02:26:09.115 --> 02:26:12.355
All these are the beginning of sorrows.

02:26:13.455 --> 02:26:21.055
Then shall they deliver you up to be afflicted, and shall kill you, and ye shall be hated

02:26:21.055 --> 02:26:23.655
of all nations for my name's sake.

02:26:24.495 --> 02:26:31.215
And then shall many be offended, and shall betray one another, and shall hate one another,

02:26:31.455 --> 02:26:36.715
and many false prophets shall rise, and shall deceive many.

02:26:37.535 --> 02:26:43.055
And because iniquity shall abound, the love of many shall wax cold.

02:26:43.835 --> 02:26:49.515
But he that shall endure unto the end, the same shall be saved.

02:26:50.295 --> 02:26:58.695
And this gospel of the kingdom shall be preached in all the world, for a witness unto all nations.

02:27:00.415 --> 02:27:02.095
And then shall the end come.

02:27:04.115 --> 02:27:10.935
When ye therefore shall see the abomination of desolation spoken of by Daniel the prophet

02:27:10.935 --> 02:27:16.035
stand in the holy place, whoso readeth, let him understand.

02:27:16.535 --> 02:27:21.395
Then let them which be in Judea flee into the mountains.

02:27:22.435 --> 02:27:28.475
Let him which is on the housetop not come down to take anything out of his house.

02:27:29.115 --> 02:27:34.815
Neither let him which is in the field return back to take his clothes.

02:27:36.015 --> 02:27:42.715
And woe unto them that are with child, and to them that give suck in those days.

02:27:43.795 --> 02:27:50.835
But pray ye that your flight be not in the winter, neither on the Sabbath day.

02:27:52.055 --> 02:27:55.275
For then shall be great tribulation.

02:27:56.395 --> 02:28:02.755
Such as was not since the beginning of the world to this time, no, nor ever shall be.

02:28:03.415 --> 02:28:06.355
And except those days should be shortened.

02:28:07.495 --> 02:28:09.515
There should no flesh be saved.

02:28:10.245 --> 02:28:14.535
But for the elect's sake those days shall be shortened.

02:28:17.095 --> 02:28:23.415
Then if any man shall say unto you, Lo, here is Christ, or there, believe it not.

02:28:24.195 --> 02:28:32.935
For there shall arise false Christs and false prophets, and shall show great signs and wonders,

02:28:33.695 --> 02:28:38.875
in so much that if it were possible, they shall deceive the very elect.

02:28:39.915 --> 02:28:41.805
Behold, I have told you before.

02:28:43.295 --> 02:28:49.875
Wherefore, if they shall say unto you, Behold, he is in the desert, go not forth.

02:28:50.455 --> 02:28:55.215
Behold, he is in the secret chambers, believe it not.

02:28:56.095 --> 02:29:01.335
For as the lightning cometh out of the east, and shineth even unto the west,

02:29:01.955 --> 02:29:04.985
so shall also the coming of the Son of Man be.

02:29:05.805 --> 02:29:11.325
For wheresoever the carcass is, there will the eagles be gathered together.

02:29:12.145 --> 02:29:17.285
Immediately after the tribulation of those days shall the sun be darkened,

02:29:18.425 --> 02:29:24.045
and the moon shall not give her light, and the stars shall fall from heaven,

02:29:24.965 --> 02:29:28.025
and the powers of the heavens shall be shaken,

02:29:29.505 --> 02:29:33.985
and then shall appear the sign of the Son of Man in heaven.

02:29:34.985 --> 02:29:38.385
And then shall all the tribes of the earth mourn,

02:29:40.125 --> 02:29:46.725
and they shall see the Son of Man coming in the clouds of heaven, with power and great glory,

02:29:46.985 --> 02:29:51.945
and he shall send his angels with a great sound of a trumpet,

02:29:52.125 --> 02:29:59.505
and they shall gather together his elect from the four winds, from one end of heaven to the other.

02:30:00.085 --> 02:30:03.125
Now learn a parable of the fig tree.

02:30:03.685 --> 02:30:09.745
When his branch is yet tender, and putteth forth leaves, ye know that summer is nigh.

02:30:10.405 --> 02:30:19.145
So likewise ye, when ye shall see all these things, know that it is near, even at the doors.

02:30:20.045 --> 02:30:27.625
Verily I say unto you, this generation shall not pass till all these things be fulfilled.

02:30:28.465 --> 02:30:37.285
Heaven and earth shall pass away, but my words shall not pass away, for of that day and hour

02:30:37.285 --> 02:30:45.925
knoweth no man, no, not the angels of heaven, but my Father only. But as the days of Noah were,

02:30:46.685 --> 02:30:53.305
so shall also the coming of the Son of Man be. For as in the days that were before the flood

02:30:53.305 --> 02:30:58.925
they were eating and drinking, marrying and giving in marriage until the day that Noah

02:30:58.925 --> 02:31:05.265
entered into the ark, and knew not until the flood came, and took them all away.

02:31:05.825 --> 02:31:13.085
So shall also the coming of the Son of Man be. Then two shall be in the field,

02:31:13.805 --> 02:31:20.225
the one shall be taken, and the other left, two women shall be grinding at the mill,

02:31:20.885 --> 02:31:29.305
the one shall be taken, and the other left. Watch therefore, for ye know not what hour

02:31:29.305 --> 02:31:37.505
your Lord doth come, but know this, that if the good man of the house had known in which watch

02:31:37.505 --> 02:31:44.365
the thief would come, he would have watched, and would not have suffered his house to be broken up.

02:31:45.105 --> 02:31:53.185
Therefore be ye also ready, for in such an hour as ye think not the Son of Man cometh.

02:31:54.565 --> 02:32:00.725
Who then is a faithful and wise servant, whom his Lord hath made ruler over his household,

02:32:01.225 --> 02:32:08.205
to give them meat in due season? Blessed is that servant, whom his Lord,

02:32:08.205 --> 02:32:16.245
when he cometh, shall find so doing. Verily I say unto you, that he shall make him ruler

02:32:16.245 --> 02:32:24.165
over all his goods. But and if that evil servant shall say in his heart, My Lord delayeth his

02:32:24.165 --> 02:32:31.865
coming, and shall begin to smite his fellow servants, and to eat and drink with the drunken.

02:32:32.765 --> 02:32:41.325
The Lord of that servant shall come in a day when he looketh not for him, and in an hour that he is

02:32:41.325 --> 02:32:49.105
not aware of, and shall cut him asunder, and appoint him his portion with the hypocrites.

02:32:50.325 --> 02:32:53.205
There shall be weeping and gnashing of teeth.

02:33:02.105 --> 02:33:02.805
you

02:33:16.031 --> 02:33:22.111
Then shall the kingdom of heaven be likened unto ten virgins, which took their lamps,

02:33:22.491 --> 02:33:24.791
and went forth to meet the bridegroom.

02:33:25.191 --> 02:33:29.511
And five of them were wise, and five were foolish.

02:33:30.491 --> 02:33:36.251
They that were foolish took their lamps, and took no oil with them.

02:33:37.011 --> 02:33:40.911
But the wise took oil in their vessels with their lamps.

02:33:41.651 --> 02:33:45.771
While the bridegroom tarried, they all slumbered and slept.

02:33:46.531 --> 02:33:51.411
And at midnight there was a cry made, Behold, the bridegroom cometh,

02:33:51.911 --> 02:33:53.631
go ye out to meet him.

02:33:54.111 --> 02:33:57.691
And all those virgins arose and trimmed their lamps.

02:33:57.691 --> 02:34:05.251
And the foolish said unto the wise, Give us of your oil, for our lamps are gone out.

02:34:06.031 --> 02:34:12.331
But the wise answered, saying, Not so, lest there be not enough for us and you,

02:34:12.591 --> 02:34:16.911
but go ye rather to them that sell and buy for yourselves.

02:34:17.951 --> 02:34:21.651
And while they went to buy, the bridegroom came,

02:34:22.311 --> 02:34:26.271
and they that were ready went in with him to the marriage.

02:34:26.271 --> 02:34:28.591
And the door was shut.

02:34:28.991 --> 02:34:34.211
Afterward came also the other virgins, saying, Lord, Lord, open to us.

02:34:34.891 --> 02:34:40.771
But he answered and said, Verily I say unto you, I know you not.

02:34:41.831 --> 02:34:48.391
Watch therefore, for ye know neither the day nor the hour wherein the Son of Man cometh.

02:34:49.031 --> 02:34:53.631
For the kingdom of heaven is as a man travelling into a far country,

02:34:53.631 --> 02:34:58.471
who called his own servants and delivered unto them his goods.

02:34:59.411 --> 02:35:06.371
And unto one he gave five talents, to another two, and to another one,

02:35:06.851 --> 02:35:12.051
to every man according to his several ability, and straightway took his journey.

02:35:12.751 --> 02:35:18.131
Then he that had received the five talents went and traded with the same,

02:35:19.271 --> 02:35:21.431
and made them other five talents.

02:35:21.431 --> 02:35:27.211
And likewise he that had received two, he also gained other two.

02:35:28.491 --> 02:35:35.211
But he that had received one went and digged in the earth and hid his Lord's money.

02:35:35.991 --> 02:35:40.851
After a long time the Lord of those servants cometh and reckoneth with them.

02:35:41.751 --> 02:35:46.991
And so he that had received five talents came and brought the other five talents,

02:35:46.991 --> 02:35:51.511
saying, Lord, thou deliverest unto me five talents.

02:35:52.111 --> 02:35:55.611
Behold, I have gained beside them five talents more.

02:35:56.571 --> 02:36:01.691
His Lord said unto him, Well done, thou good and faithful servant.

02:36:02.491 --> 02:36:05.671
Thou hast been faithful over a few things.

02:36:05.871 --> 02:36:08.791
I will make thee ruler over many things.

02:36:09.331 --> 02:36:11.851
Enter thou into the joy of thy Lord.

02:36:13.091 --> 02:36:18.691
He also that had received two talents came and said, Lord,

02:36:19.271 --> 02:36:21.611
thou deliverest unto me two talents.

02:36:22.071 --> 02:36:25.851
Behold, I have gained two other talents beside them.

02:36:26.711 --> 02:36:32.011
His Lord said unto him, Well done, good and faithful servant.

02:36:32.751 --> 02:36:35.771
Thou hast been faithful over a few things.

02:36:36.531 --> 02:36:39.331
I will make thee ruler over many things.

02:36:39.331 --> 02:36:42.791
Enter thou into the joy of thy Lord.

02:36:43.611 --> 02:36:48.271
Then he which had received the one talent came and said, Lord,

02:36:48.751 --> 02:36:55.411
I knew thee that thou art an hard man, reaping where thou hast not sown

02:36:55.411 --> 02:36:58.891
and gathering where thou hast not strawed.

02:36:59.491 --> 02:37:04.631
And I was afraid, and went and hid thy talent in the earth.

02:37:05.011 --> 02:37:07.651
Lo, there thou hast that is thine.

02:37:08.371 --> 02:37:14.191
His Lord answered and said unto him, Thou wicked and slothful servant.

02:37:15.211 --> 02:37:22.731
Thou knewest that I reap where I sow not and gather where I have not strawed.

02:37:22.931 --> 02:37:27.011
Thou oughtest therefore to have put my money to the exchangers.

02:37:28.071 --> 02:37:32.291
And then at my coming I should have received mine own with usury.

02:37:33.231 --> 02:37:39.411
Take therefore the talent from him, and give it unto him which hath ten talents.

02:37:40.671 --> 02:37:46.151
For unto every one that hath shall be given, and he shall have an abundance.

02:37:46.691 --> 02:37:52.461
But from him that hath not shall be taken away even that which he hath.

02:37:53.811 --> 02:37:59.211
And cast ye the unprofitable servant into outer darkness.

02:37:59.211 --> 02:38:02.471
There shall be weeping and gnashing of teeth.

02:38:03.671 --> 02:38:09.671
When the Son of Man shall come in his glory, and all the holy angels with him,

02:38:10.511 --> 02:38:17.851
then shall he sit upon the throne of his glory, and before him shall be gathered all nations,

02:38:18.331 --> 02:38:25.071
and he shall separate them one from another, as a shepherd divideth his sheep from the goats.

02:38:25.071 --> 02:38:31.911
And he shall set the sheep on his right hand, but the goats on the left.

02:38:32.551 --> 02:38:38.811
Then shall the King say unto them on his right hand, Come, ye blessed of my Father,

02:38:39.531 --> 02:38:43.511
inherit the kingdom prepared for you from the foundation of the world.

02:38:45.231 --> 02:38:52.491
For I was unhungred, and ye gave me meat, I was thirsty, and ye gave me drink.

02:38:52.491 --> 02:38:57.911
I was a stranger, and ye took me in, naked, and ye clothed me.

02:38:57.991 --> 02:39:00.811
I was sick, and ye visited me.

02:39:01.651 --> 02:39:04.951
I was in prison, and ye came unto me.

02:39:07.311 --> 02:39:11.871
Then shall the righteous answer him, saying, Lord, when saw we thee,

02:39:11.871 --> 02:39:15.871
and hungred, and fed thee, or thirsty, and gave thee drink?

02:39:16.211 --> 02:39:21.851
When saw we thee a stranger, and took thee in, or naked, and clothed thee?

02:39:21.851 --> 02:39:26.951
Or when saw we thee sick, or in prison, and came unto thee?

02:39:28.231 --> 02:39:33.931
And the King shall answer, and say unto them, Verily, I say unto you,

02:39:34.831 --> 02:39:39.831
Inasmuch as ye have done it unto one of the least of these my brethren,

02:39:41.031 --> 02:39:42.831
ye have done it unto me.

02:39:43.451 --> 02:39:50.791
Then shall he say also unto them on the left hand, Depart from me, ye cursed.

02:39:51.851 --> 02:39:56.171
Into everlasting fire, prepared for the devil and his angels.

02:39:57.371 --> 02:40:03.931
For I was unhungred, and ye gave me no meat, I was thirsty, and ye gave me no drink.

02:40:04.731 --> 02:40:10.571
I was a stranger, and ye took me not in, naked, and ye clothed me not.

02:40:10.591 --> 02:40:14.751
I was sick, and in prison, and ye visited me not.

02:40:15.931 --> 02:40:21.591
Then shall they also answer him, saying, Lord, when saw we thee,

02:40:21.591 --> 02:40:25.591
and hungred, or a thirst, or a stranger, or naked, or sick,

02:40:26.011 --> 02:40:29.691
or in prison, and did not minister unto thee?

02:40:31.231 --> 02:40:35.931
Then shall he answer them, saying, Verily, I say unto you,

02:40:36.771 --> 02:40:43.311
Inasmuch as ye did it not to one of the least of these, ye did it not to me,

02:40:43.311 --> 02:40:48.731
and these shall go away into everlasting punishment,

02:40:50.551 --> 02:40:53.911
but the righteous into life eternal.

02:41:15.473 --> 02:41:22.553
And it came to pass, when Jesus had finished all these sayings, he said unto his disciples,

02:41:23.393 --> 02:41:30.453
Ye know that after two days is the feast of the Passover, and the Son of Man is betrayed

02:41:30.453 --> 02:41:31.593
to be crucified.

02:41:32.353 --> 02:41:38.153
Then assembled together the chief priests and the scribes and the elders of the people unto

02:41:38.153 --> 02:41:44.673
the palace of the high priest who was called Caiaphas, and consulted that they might take

02:41:44.673 --> 02:41:47.773
Jesus by subtlety and kill him.

02:41:48.793 --> 02:41:54.153
But they said, not on the feast day, lest there be an uproar among the people.

02:41:54.793 --> 02:42:01.513
Now when Jesus was in Bethany, in the house of Simon the leper, there came unto him a woman,

02:42:01.513 --> 02:42:09.513
having an alabaster box of very precious ointment, and poured it on his head as he sat at meat.

02:42:09.773 --> 02:42:16.533
But when his disciples saw it, they had indignation, saying, To what purpose is this waste?

02:42:16.993 --> 02:42:22.613
For this ointment might have been sold for much and given to the poor.

02:42:23.453 --> 02:42:28.273
When Jesus understood it, he said unto them, Why trouble ye this woman?

02:42:29.113 --> 02:42:32.653
For she hath wrought a good work upon me.

02:42:33.073 --> 02:42:38.793
For ye have the poor always with you, but me ye have not always.

02:42:40.193 --> 02:42:45.613
For in that she hath poured this ointment on my body, she did it for my burial.

02:42:46.713 --> 02:42:53.313
Verily I say unto you, wheresoever this gospel shall be preached in the whole world,

02:42:53.313 --> 02:42:59.273
there shall also this that this woman hath done be told for a memorial of her.

02:42:59.833 --> 02:43:07.093
Then one of the twelve, called Judas Iscariot, went unto the chief priests, and said unto them,

02:43:08.073 --> 02:43:12.473
What will ye give me? And I will deliver him unto you.

02:43:12.773 --> 02:43:16.513
And they covenanted with him for thirty pieces of silver.

02:43:17.353 --> 02:43:22.633
And from that time he sought opportunity to betray him.

02:43:22.633 --> 02:43:29.473
Now the first day of the feast of unleavened bread the disciples came to Jesus, saying unto him,

02:43:29.833 --> 02:43:33.393
Where wilt thou, that we prepare for thee to eat the Passover?

02:43:34.993 --> 02:43:40.253
And he said, Go into the city to such a man, and say unto him,

02:43:40.513 --> 02:43:47.613
The Master saith, My time is at hand, I will keep the Passover at thy house with my disciples.

02:43:47.613 --> 02:43:53.993
And the disciples did as Jesus had appointed them, and they made ready the Passover.

02:43:55.073 --> 02:43:59.533
Now when the even was come, he sat down with the twelve.

02:44:00.713 --> 02:44:08.113
And as they did eat he said, Verily I say unto you, that one of you shall betray me.

02:44:08.373 --> 02:44:15.193
And they were exceeding sorrowful, and began every one of them to say unto him,

02:44:15.193 --> 02:44:16.813
Lord, is it I?

02:44:18.113 --> 02:44:26.413
And he answered and said, He that dippeth his hand with me in the dish, the same shall betray me.

02:44:28.173 --> 02:44:31.433
The Son of Man goeth, as it is written of him.

02:44:32.393 --> 02:44:36.373
But woe unto that man by whom the Son of Man is betrayed!

02:44:37.213 --> 02:44:40.873
It had been good for that man if he had not been born.

02:44:41.713 --> 02:44:47.853
Then Judas, which betrayed him, answered and said, Master, is it I?

02:44:48.913 --> 02:44:52.273
He said unto him, Thou hast said.

02:44:53.073 --> 02:44:59.113
And as they were eating, Jesus took bread, and blessed it, and break it,

02:44:59.673 --> 02:45:06.653
and gave it to the disciples, and said, Take, eat, this is my body.

02:45:07.773 --> 02:45:15.893
And he took the cup, and gave thanks, and gave it to them, saying, Drink ye all of it,

02:45:16.213 --> 02:45:23.453
for this is my blood of the New Testament, which is shed for many for the remission of sins.

02:45:24.473 --> 02:45:30.733
But I say unto you, I will not drink henceforth of this fruit of the vine,

02:45:31.393 --> 02:45:36.333
until that day when I drink it new with you in my Father's kingdom.

02:45:36.333 --> 02:45:42.153
And when they had sung an hymn, they went out into the Mount of Olives.

02:45:43.153 --> 02:45:49.033
Then saith Jesus unto them, All ye shall be offended because of me this night.

02:45:49.853 --> 02:45:57.073
For it is written, I will smite the shepherd, and the sheep of the flock shall be scattered abroad.

02:45:58.173 --> 02:46:03.073
But after I am risen again, I will go before you into Galilee.

02:46:04.513 --> 02:46:10.993
But Peter answered, and said unto him, Thou all men shall be offended because of thee,

02:46:11.273 --> 02:46:19.313
yet will I never be offended. Jesus said unto him, Verily I say unto thee,

02:46:19.633 --> 02:46:26.273
that this night, before the cock crow, thou shalt deny me thrice.

02:46:27.413 --> 02:46:34.133
Peter said unto him, Though I should die with thee, yet will I not deny thee.

02:46:34.933 --> 02:46:37.993
Likewise also said all the disciples.

02:46:40.273 --> 02:46:47.133
Then cometh Jesus with them unto a place called Gethsemane, and saith unto the disciples,

02:46:47.573 --> 02:46:56.193
Sit ye here, while I go and pray yonder. And he took with him Peter, and the two sons of Zebedee,

02:46:56.913 --> 02:47:05.513
And began to be sorrowful and very heavy. He saith unto them, My soul is exceeding sorrowful,

02:47:05.833 --> 02:47:10.073
even unto death. Carry ye here and watch with me.

02:47:10.413 --> 02:47:18.553
And he went a little farther, and fell on his face, and prayed, saying, O my father,

02:47:19.493 --> 02:47:29.673
If it be possible, let this cup pass from me, nevertheless, not as I will, but as thou wilt.

02:47:30.753 --> 02:47:35.193
And he cometh unto the disciples, and findeth them asleep.

02:47:36.153 --> 02:47:41.173
And saith unto Peter, What, could ye not watch with me one hour?

02:47:41.893 --> 02:47:49.673
Watch and pray, that ye enter not into temptation. The spirit indeed is willing,

02:47:50.133 --> 02:47:59.353
but the flesh is weak. He went away again the second time, and prayed, saying, O my father,

02:47:59.913 --> 02:48:07.153
If this cup may not pass away from me, except I drink it, thy will be done.

02:48:08.533 --> 02:48:13.753
And he came, and found them asleep again, for their eyes were heavy.

02:48:14.773 --> 02:48:20.653
And he left them, and went away again, and prayed the third time, saying the same words.

02:48:21.873 --> 02:48:29.013
Then cometh he to his disciples, and saith unto them, Sleep on now, and take your rest.

02:48:29.913 --> 02:48:37.133
Behold, the hour is at hand, and the Son of Man is betrayed into the hands of sinners.

02:48:38.173 --> 02:48:45.493
Rise, let us be going. Behold, he is at hand that doth betray me.

02:48:46.793 --> 02:48:53.933
And while he yet spake, lo, Judas, one of the twelve, came, and with him a great multitude

02:48:53.933 --> 02:48:59.873
with swords and staves, from the chief priests and elders of the people.

02:49:00.553 --> 02:49:07.133
Now he that betrayed him gave them a sign, saying, Whomsoever I shall kiss, that soon

02:49:07.133 --> 02:49:18.053
as he hold him fast. And forthwith he came to Jesus, and said, Hail, Master, and kissed him.

02:49:19.313 --> 02:49:23.993
And Jesus said unto him, Friend, wherefore art thou come?

02:49:25.493 --> 02:49:32.173
Then came they, and laid hands on Jesus, and took him. And, behold, one of them,

02:49:32.173 --> 02:49:36.573
which were with Jesus, stretched out his hand, and drew his sword,

02:49:37.073 --> 02:49:41.613
and struck a servant of the high priest, and smote off his ear.

02:49:42.773 --> 02:49:47.873
Then Jesus said unto him, Put up again thy sword into his place,

02:49:48.813 --> 02:49:52.773
for all they that take the sword shall perish with the sword.

02:49:54.633 --> 02:50:00.953
Thinkest thou that I cannot now pray to my Father, and he shall presently give me more than twelve

02:50:00.953 --> 02:50:09.093
legions of angels? But how then shall the Scriptures be fulfilled, that thus it must be?

02:50:10.473 --> 02:50:17.853
In that same hour said Jesus to the multitudes, Are ye come out as against a thief,

02:50:18.233 --> 02:50:24.753
with swords and staves, for to take me? I sat daily with you teaching in the temple,

02:50:25.373 --> 02:50:32.513
and ye laid no hold on me. But all this was done, that the Scriptures of the prophets

02:50:32.513 --> 02:50:42.573
might be fulfilled. Then all the disciples forsook him, and fled. And they that had laid hold on Jesus

02:50:43.013 --> 02:50:49.313
led him away to Caiaphas the high priest, where the scribes and the elders were assembled.

02:50:50.513 --> 02:50:55.333
But Peter followed him afar off unto the high priest's palace,

02:50:56.013 --> 02:51:03.233
and went in and sat with the servants to see the end. Now the chief priests, and elders,

02:51:03.433 --> 02:51:10.813
and all the council, sought false witness against Jesus, to put him to death. But found none,

02:51:11.093 --> 02:51:19.293
yea, though many false witnesses came, yet found they none. At the last came two false witnesses,

02:51:20.053 --> 02:51:28.913
and said, This fellow said, I am able to destroy the temple of God, and to build it in three days.

02:51:30.313 --> 02:51:38.033
And the high priest arose, and said unto him, Answerest thou nothing? What is it which these

02:51:38.033 --> 02:51:45.093
witness against thee? But Jesus held his peace. And the high priest answered and said unto him,

02:51:45.093 --> 02:51:53.973
I adjure thee by the living God, that thou tellest whether thou be the Christ, the Son of God.

02:51:55.393 --> 02:52:04.653
Jesus saith unto him, Thou hast said, Nevertheless I say unto you, Hereafter ye shall see the Son

02:52:04.653 --> 02:52:14.573
of Man sitting on the right hand of power, and coming in the clouds of heaven. Then the high

02:52:14.573 --> 02:52:23.393
priest said unto him, What further need have we of witnesses? Behold, now ye have heard his blasphemy,

02:52:23.773 --> 02:52:32.133
what think ye? They answered and said, He is guilty of death. Then did they spit in his face,

02:52:32.593 --> 02:52:38.673
and buffeted him, and others smoked him with the palms of their hands, saying,

02:52:38.673 --> 02:52:43.893
Prophecy untoest thou Christ? Who is he that smoked thee?

02:52:44.893 --> 02:52:52.253
Now Peter sat without in the palace, and a damsel came unto him, saying, Thou also wast with Jesus

02:52:52.253 --> 02:52:59.353
of Galilee. But he denied before them all, saying, I know not what thou sayest.

02:53:00.593 --> 02:53:07.653
And when he was gone out into the porch, another maid saw him, and said unto them that were there,

02:53:07.653 --> 02:53:15.813
This fellow was also with Jesus of Nazareth. And again he denied with an oath, I do not know the

02:53:15.813 --> 02:53:25.393
man. And after a while came unto him they that stood by, and said to Peter, Surely thou also art

02:53:25.393 --> 02:53:34.013
one of them, for thy speech berayeth thee. Then began he to curse, and to swear, saying, I know

02:53:34.013 --> 02:53:41.313
not the man. And immediately the cock crew, and Peter remembered the word of Jesus,

02:53:42.093 --> 02:53:48.813
which said unto him, Before the cock crow thou shalt deny me thrice.

02:53:50.853 --> 02:53:54.493
And he went out, and wept bitterly.

02:54:16.899 --> 02:54:23.999
When the morning was come, all the chief priests and elders of the people took counsel against

02:54:23.999 --> 02:54:26.639
Jesus to put him to death.

02:54:27.439 --> 02:54:33.699
And when they had bound him, they led him away and delivered him to Pontius Pilate the

02:54:33.699 --> 02:54:33.939
governor.

02:54:34.959 --> 02:54:41.939
Then Judas, which had betrayed him, when he saw that he was condemned, repented himself,

02:54:42.479 --> 02:54:48.919
and brought again the thirty pieces of silver to the chief priests and elders, saying, I

02:54:48.919 --> 02:54:53.159
have sinned, and that I have betrayed the innocent blood.

02:54:54.079 --> 02:54:56.799
And they said, What is that to us?

02:54:57.279 --> 02:54:58.599
See thou to that.

02:54:59.379 --> 02:55:06.299
And he cast down the pieces of silver in the temple, and departed, and went, and hanged

02:55:06.299 --> 02:55:06.999
himself.

02:55:07.679 --> 02:55:14.299
And the chief priests took the silver pieces, and said, It is not lawful, for to put them

02:55:14.299 --> 02:55:17.219
into the treasury, because it is the price of blood.

02:55:18.079 --> 02:55:24.199
And they took counsel, and bought with them the potter's field, to bury strangers in.

02:55:24.199 --> 02:55:29.379
Wherefore that field was called the field of blood unto this day.

02:55:30.879 --> 02:55:36.719
Then was fulfilled that which was spoken by Jeremy the prophet, saying, And they took

02:55:36.719 --> 02:55:43.739
the thirty pieces of silver, the price of him that was valued, whom they of the children

02:55:43.739 --> 02:55:50.119
of Israel did value, and gave them for the potter's field, as the Lord appointed me.

02:55:50.659 --> 02:55:56.839
And Jesus stood before the governor, and the governor asked him, saying, Art thou the king

02:55:56.839 --> 02:55:57.539
of the Jews?

02:55:58.499 --> 02:56:01.799
And Jesus said unto him, Thou sayest.

02:56:02.559 --> 02:56:07.539
And when he was accused of the chief priests and elders, he answered nothing.

02:56:09.019 --> 02:56:15.159
Then said Pilate unto him, Hearest thou not how many things they witness against thee?

02:56:15.159 --> 02:56:21.199
And he answered him to never a word, insomuch that the governor marveled greatly.

02:56:21.939 --> 02:56:27.359
Now at that feast the governor was wont to release unto the people a prisoner whom they

02:56:27.359 --> 02:56:27.739
would.

02:56:28.299 --> 02:56:31.759
And they had then a notable prisoner, called Barabbas.

02:56:32.099 --> 02:56:38.539
Therefore when they were gathered together, Pilate said unto them, Whom will ye that I

02:56:38.539 --> 02:56:44.319
release unto you, Barabbas, or Jesus, which is called Christ?

02:56:44.679 --> 02:56:48.579
For he knew that for envy they had delivered him.

02:56:50.059 --> 02:56:56.579
When he was sat down on the judgment seat, his wife sent unto him, saying, Hav thou nothing

02:56:56.579 --> 02:56:58.499
to do with that just man?

02:56:59.119 --> 02:57:04.179
For I have suffered many things this day in a dream because of him.

02:57:05.799 --> 02:57:12.579
But the chief priests and elders persuaded the multitude that they should ask Barabbas

02:57:12.579 --> 02:57:14.839
and destroy Jesus.

02:57:15.739 --> 02:57:22.159
The governor asked and said unto them, Whither of the twain will ye that I release unto you?

02:57:22.279 --> 02:57:24.799
And they said, Barabbas.

02:57:25.839 --> 02:57:31.619
Pilate saith unto them, What shall I do then with Jesus, which is called Christ?

02:57:32.519 --> 02:57:36.299
They all say unto him, Let him be crucified.

02:57:38.209 --> 02:57:40.439
And the governor said, Why?

02:57:40.439 --> 02:57:42.539
What evil hath he done?

02:57:42.859 --> 02:57:47.439
But they cried all the more, saying, Let him be crucified.

02:57:48.999 --> 02:57:56.019
When Pilate saw that he could prevail nothing, but that rather a tumult was made, he took

02:57:56.019 --> 02:58:03.239
water and washed his hands before the multitude, saying, I am innocent of the blood of this

02:58:03.239 --> 02:58:04.259
just person.

02:58:05.159 --> 02:58:06.399
See ye to it.

02:58:07.079 --> 02:58:13.879
Then answered all the people, and said, His blood be on us and on our children.

02:58:15.119 --> 02:58:17.719
Then released he Barabbas unto them.

02:58:18.479 --> 02:58:24.659
And when he had scourged Jesus, he delivered him to be crucified.

02:58:25.559 --> 02:58:32.339
Then the soldiers of the governor took Jesus into the common hall, and gathered unto him

02:58:32.339 --> 02:58:34.459
the whole band of soldiers.

02:58:35.059 --> 02:58:39.539
And they stripped him, and put on him a scarlet robe.

02:58:40.179 --> 02:58:47.199
And when they had platted a crown of thorns, they put it upon his head, and a reed in his

02:58:47.199 --> 02:58:48.119
right hand.

02:58:48.299 --> 02:58:53.939
And they bowed the knee before him, and mocked him, saying, Hail, King of the Jews!

02:58:54.539 --> 02:59:00.399
And they spit upon him, and took the reed, and smote him on the head.

02:59:01.099 --> 02:59:08.259
And after that they had mocked him, they took the robe off from him, and put his own raiment

02:59:08.259 --> 02:59:12.319
on him, and led him away to crucify him.

02:59:13.299 --> 02:59:20.239
And as they came out, they found a man of Cyrene, Simon by name, him they compelled

02:59:20.239 --> 02:59:21.919
to bear his cross.

02:59:23.059 --> 02:59:30.059
And when they were come unto a place called Golgotha, that is to say, a place of a skull,

02:59:30.559 --> 02:59:34.099
they gave him vinegar to drink, mingled with gall.

02:59:35.159 --> 02:59:38.999
And when he had tasted thereof, he would not drink.

02:59:40.459 --> 02:59:47.099
And they crucified him, and parted his garments, casting lots, that it might be fulfilled which

02:59:47.099 --> 02:59:48.699
was spoken by the prophet.

02:59:49.309 --> 02:59:56.339
They parted my garments among them, and upon my vesture did they cast lots.

02:59:57.299 --> 03:00:00.519
And sitting down, they watched him there.

03:00:01.579 --> 03:00:09.239
And set up over his head his accusation written, This is Jesus, the King of the Jews!

03:00:10.019 --> 03:00:16.739
Then were there two thieves crucified with him, one on the right hand, and another on

03:00:16.739 --> 03:00:17.519
the left.

03:00:17.979 --> 03:00:25.939
And they that passed by reviled him, wagging their heads, and saying, Thou that destroyest

03:00:25.939 --> 03:00:30.399
the temple, and buildest it in three days, save thyself!

03:00:30.959 --> 03:00:35.559
If thou be the Son of God, come down from the cross.

03:00:36.859 --> 03:00:43.639
Likewise also the chief priests mocking him, with the scribes and elders said, He saved

03:00:43.639 --> 03:00:46.999
others, himself he cannot save.

03:00:47.919 --> 03:00:55.939
If he be the King of Israel, let him now come down from the cross, and we will believe him.

03:00:56.519 --> 03:00:58.299
He trusted in God.

03:00:59.099 --> 03:01:06.339
Let him deliver him now, if he will have him, for he said, I am the Son of God.

03:01:07.339 --> 03:01:13.299
The thieves also, which were crucified with him, cast the same in his teeth.

03:01:14.379 --> 03:01:20.999
Now about the sixth hour there was darkness over all the land unto the ninth hour.

03:01:22.179 --> 03:01:32.979
And about the ninth hour Jesus cried with a loud voice, saying, Eli, Eli, Lama sabachthani!

03:01:33.739 --> 03:01:39.319
That is to say, My God, my God, why hast thou forsaken me?

03:01:39.839 --> 03:01:45.699
Some of them that stood there, when they heard that said, This man calleth for Elias.

03:01:46.299 --> 03:01:52.399
And straightway one of them ran, and took a sponge, and filled it with vinegar, and

03:01:52.399 --> 03:01:55.599
put it on a reed, and gave him to drink.

03:01:56.519 --> 03:02:03.859
The rest said, Let be, let us see whether Elias will come to save him.

03:02:04.599 --> 03:02:11.859
Jesus, when he had cried again with a loud voice, yielded up the ghost.

03:02:12.739 --> 03:02:20.059
And behold, the veil of the temple was rent in twain, from the top to the bottom, and

03:02:20.059 --> 03:02:25.919
the earth did quake, and the rocks rent, and the graves were opened.

03:02:26.339 --> 03:02:32.999
And many bodies of the saints which slept arose, and came out of the graves after his

03:02:32.999 --> 03:02:38.539
resurrection, and went into the holy city, and appeared unto many.

03:02:39.099 --> 03:02:45.139
Now when the centurion and they that were with him watching Jesus saw the earthquake

03:02:45.139 --> 03:02:51.599
and those things that were done, they feared greatly, saying, Truly, this was the Son of

03:02:51.599 --> 03:02:52.239
God.

03:02:53.239 --> 03:02:59.839
And many women were there beholding afar off, which followed Jesus from Galilee, ministering

03:02:59.839 --> 03:03:06.579
unto him, among which was Mary Magdalene, and Mary the mother of James and Joses, and

03:03:06.579 --> 03:03:08.299
the mother of Zebedee's children.

03:03:08.299 --> 03:03:16.339
When the even was come, there came a rich man of Arimathea named Joseph, who also himself

03:03:16.339 --> 03:03:17.959
was Jesus' disciple.

03:03:19.159 --> 03:03:22.959
He went to Pilate, and begged the body of Jesus.

03:03:23.899 --> 03:03:26.679
Then Pilate commanded the body to be delivered.

03:03:27.539 --> 03:03:34.779
And when Joseph had taken the body, he wrapped it in a clean linen cloth, and laid it in

03:03:34.779 --> 03:03:42.379
his own new tomb, which he had hewn out of the rock, and he rolled a great stone to the

03:03:42.379 --> 03:03:44.859
door of the sepulcher, and departed.

03:03:45.659 --> 03:03:50.259
And there was Mary Magdalene, and the other Mary sitting over against the sepulcher.

03:03:50.779 --> 03:03:58.139
Now the next day, that followed the day of the preparation, the chief priests and Pharisees

03:03:59.199 --> 03:04:06.619
Pilate, saying, Sir, we remember, that that deceiver said while he was yet alive, After

03:04:06.619 --> 03:04:09.099
three days I will rise again.

03:04:10.199 --> 03:04:17.639
Command therefore, that the sepulcher be made sure, until the third day, lest his disciples

03:04:17.639 --> 03:04:25.279
come by night, and steal him away, and say unto the people, He is risen from the dead.

03:04:25.979 --> 03:04:30.139
So the last error shall be worse than the first.

03:04:30.839 --> 03:04:38.159
Pilate said unto them, Ye have a watch, go your way, make it as sure as ye can.

03:04:39.859 --> 03:04:47.079
So they went, and made the sepulcher sure, sealing the stone, and setting a watch.

03:05:09.627 --> 03:05:15.547
In the end of the Sabbath, as it began to dawn toward the first day of the week, came

03:05:15.547 --> 03:05:22.147
Mary Magdalene and the other Mary to see the sepulcher, and, behold, there was a great

03:05:22.147 --> 03:05:22.967
earthquake.

03:05:24.047 --> 03:05:30.627
For the angel of the Lord descended from heaven, and came and rolled back the stone from the

03:05:30.627 --> 03:05:33.187
door, and sat upon it.

03:05:33.547 --> 03:05:38.867
His countenance was like lightning, and his raiment white as snow.

03:05:40.207 --> 03:05:44.887
And for fear of him the keepers did shake, and became as dead men.

03:05:45.447 --> 03:05:53.527
And the angel answered and said unto the women, Fear not ye, for I know that ye seek Jesus,

03:05:53.907 --> 03:05:55.487
which was crucified.

03:05:55.867 --> 03:06:04.427
He is not here, for he is risen, as he said, Come, see the place where the Lord lay.

03:06:04.907 --> 03:06:13.007
And go quickly, and tell his disciples that he is risen from the dead, and, behold, he

03:06:13.007 --> 03:06:15.587
goeth before you into Galilee.

03:06:16.127 --> 03:06:21.387
There ye shall see him, lo, I have told you.

03:06:21.387 --> 03:06:27.987
And they departed quickly from the sepulcher with fear and great joy, and did run to bring

03:06:27.987 --> 03:06:29.627
his disciples word.

03:06:30.507 --> 03:06:37.907
And as they went to tell his disciples, behold, Jesus met them, saying, All hail!

03:06:38.287 --> 03:06:42.387
And they came and held him by the feet, and worshiped him.

03:06:42.867 --> 03:06:46.647
Then said Jesus unto them, Be not afraid.

03:06:47.467 --> 03:06:53.147
Go tell my brethren that they go into Galilee, and there shall they see me.

03:06:53.807 --> 03:07:00.767
Now when they were going, behold, some of the watch came into the city, and showed unto

03:07:00.767 --> 03:07:03.607
the chief priests all the things that were done.

03:07:04.197 --> 03:07:10.787
And when they were assembled with the elders, and had taken counsel, they gave large money

03:07:10.787 --> 03:07:18.207
unto the soldiers, saying, Say ye, his disciples came by night, and stole him away while we

03:07:18.207 --> 03:07:18.707
slept.

03:07:20.047 --> 03:07:26.167
And if this come to the governor's ears, we will persuade him, and secure you.

03:07:26.407 --> 03:07:33.087
So they took the money, and did as they were taught, and this saying is commonly reported

03:07:33.087 --> 03:07:35.487
among the Jews until this day.

03:07:37.207 --> 03:07:44.467
Then the eleven disciples went away into Galilee, into a mountain where Jesus had appointed

03:07:44.467 --> 03:07:45.327
them.

03:07:46.107 --> 03:07:50.907
And when they saw him, they worshiped him, but some doubted.

03:07:51.107 --> 03:07:58.487
And Jesus came and spake unto them, saying, All power is given unto me, in heaven and

03:07:58.487 --> 03:07:59.227
in earth.

03:08:00.187 --> 03:08:08.347
Go ye therefore, and teach all nations, baptizing them in the name of the Father, and of the

03:08:08.347 --> 03:08:15.547
Son, and of the Holy Ghost, teaching them to observe all things whatsoever I have commanded

03:08:15.547 --> 03:08:16.207
you.

03:08:16.827 --> 03:08:23.067
And lo, I am with you always, even unto the end of the world.

03:08:23.847 --> 03:08:24.447
Amen.
